results.name: Rheumatologic Disorder
results.definition: Inflammatory and degenerative diseases of connective tissue structures, such as arthritis.
results.glossary_definition: A group of disorders marked by inflammation or pain in the connective tissue structures of the body. These structures include bone, cartilage, and fat.

results.name: Sleep Apnea
results.definition: Cessation of breathing for short periods during sleep. It is classified as obstructive, central, or mixed obstructive-central. It can occur at any age but it is more frequent in people over forty. Risk factors include male sex and obesity.
results.glossary_definition: A sleep disorder that is marked by pauses in breathing of 10 seconds or more during sleep, and causes unrestful sleep. Symptoms include loud or abnormal snoring, daytime sleepiness, irritability, and depression.

results.name: Cholelithiasis
results.definition: The presence of calculi in the gallbladder.
results.glossary_definition: The presence of calculi in the gallbladder.

results.name: Urethral Obstruction
results.definition: Blockage of the normal flow of urine in the urethra.

results.name: Bone Epithelioid Hemangioma
results.definition: A locally aggressive hemangioma that arises from the bone. It is characterized by the presence of epithelioid endothelial cells.
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Hypogonadism
results.definition: A disorder characterized by decreased function of the gonads. Clinical manifestations in both males and females include poor libido, infertility, and osteoporosis. Additional signs in males include erectile dysfunction, muscle atrophy, gynecomastia and increased abdominal fat. In females, additional signs include shrinking of the breasts and loss of, or failure to develop menstruation.

results.name: Bacterial Vaginosis
results.definition: Infection caused by bacterial overgrowth in the vagina. Most affected women are asymptomatic. When symptoms occur, they include foul-smelling vaginal discharge, vaginal itching, and burning. Risk factors include sexual activity with multiple partners and the use of vaginal douches and intrauterine devices. Up to a third of cases resolve without treatment. Antibiotic treatment is recommended when symptoms are present and for women that are pregnant at the time of infection.

results.name: Proteus Syndrome
results.definition: A very rare congenital disorder characterized by the development of multiple cutaneous and subcutaneous lesions including lipomas, nevi, and vascular malformations, associated with partial gigantism or digital overgrowth.

results.name: Periductal Breast Myoepitheliosis
results.definition: A neoplastic process characterized by the proliferation of spindle to cuboidal myoepithelial cells around small breast ducts.

results.name: Paget Disease of the Anus
results.definition: A slowly spreading, erythematous eczematoid plaque in the anal region. Histologically, the basal part or whole thickness of the squamous epithelium is infiltrated by large cells with abundant pale cytoplasm and large nuclei. Half of the cases are associated with an internal malignancy, most often a colorectal adenocarcinoma. The other half of the cases, have a high local recurrence rate and they may become invasive (WHO).

Paget Disease of the Anal Margin

results.name: Periodontitis
results.definition: An acute or chronic inflammatory process that affects the tissues that surround and support the teeth.
results.glossary_definition: Inflammatory reaction of the tissues surrounding a tooth (periodontium), usually resulting from the extension of gingival inflammation (gingivitis) into the periodontium. (From Dorland, 27th ed)

results.name: Labia Majora Carcinoma
results.definition: A carcinoma that arises from the labia majora.

results.name: Epicardial Lipoma
results.definition: A rare benign adipose tissue neoplasm of the epicardium of the heart.

results.name: Candidiasis
results.definition: Infection with the organism Candida.
results.glossary_definition: A condition in which Candida albicans, a type of yeast, grows out of control in moist skin areas of the body. It is usually a result of a weakened immune system, but can be a side effect of chemotherapy or treatment with antibiotics. Thrush usually affects the mouth (oral thrush); however, rarely, it spreads throughout the entire body.

results.name: Retinal Vascular Occlusion
results.definition: An occlusion of the retinal vasculature.

results.name: Secondary Polycythemia
results.definition: Polycythemia resulting from an elevated concentration of erythropoietin.
children: Polycythaemia due to Excess Erythropoetin Production

results.name: Toxic Nodular Goiter
results.definition: Nodular enlargement of the thyroid gland associated with hyperthyroidism.

results.name: Mitral Valve Disorder
results.definition: A heart disorder characterized by a defect in mitral valve structure or function.
results.glossary_definition: A disorder characterized by a defect in mitral valve function or structure.

results.name: Gynatresia
results.definition: A congenital or acquired occlusion of an opening in any part of the female genital tract.

Acute Promyelocytic Leukemia with t(15;17)(q22;q12); PML/RARA
ancestors: Acute Myeloid Leukemia with Recurrent Genetic Abnormalities
parents: Acute Myeloid Leukemia with Recurrent Genetic Abnormalities
results.definition: An acute myeloid leukemia (AML) in which abnormal promyelocytes predominate. It is characterized by the PML-RARA fusion. There are two variants: the typical and microgranular variant. This AML is particularly sensitive to treatment with all trans-retinoic acid and has a favorable prognosis. (WHO)
results.glossary_definition: An aggressive (fast-growing) type of acute myeloid leukemia in which there are too many immature blood-forming cells in the blood and bone marrow. It is usually marked by an exchange of parts of chromosomes 15 and 17.
results.name: Acute Promyelocytic Leukemia
Epithelioid Cell Melanoma
results.definition: A melanoma characterized by the presence of malignant large epithelioid melanocytes.

results.name: Esophageal Leukoplakia
results.definition: A rare condition that usually affects the middle-to-distal esophagus in middle-aged and elderly people. There is usually a history of tobacco smoking or alcohol intake. Dysphagia is the presenting symptom. Morphologically, the lesions are well-demarcated and are characterized by epithelial hyperplasia, thickened basal layer, prominent granular cell layer, and hyperorthokeratosis. In a minority of patients this condition is associated with adjacent high-grade squamous dysplasia and/or squamous cell carcinoma.

results.name: Mucopolysaccharidosis Type I
results.definition: The most common type of mucopolysaccharidosis. It is inherited in an autosomal recessive pattern. It comprises a group of lysosomal storage diseases which includes the most severe form (Hurler syndrome) and the mildest form (Scheie syndrome).

results.name: Ovarian Dysgerminoma
match: Germ Cell Dysgerminoma of the Ovary
search: Germ Cell Dysgerminoma of the Ovary
results.definition: A malignant germ cell tumor arising from the ovary. Morphologically, it is identical to seminoma and consists of a monotonous population of germ cells with abundant pale cytoplasm and uniform nuclei. The stroma invariably contains chronic inflammatory cells, mostly T-lymphocytes. It responds to chemotherapy or radiotherapy and the prognosis relates to the tumor stage.
synonyms: Germ Cell Dysgerminoma of the Ovary

results.name: Prostate Adenoma
results.definition: Focal benign glandular hyperplasia in the prostate gland.

results.name: Anal Canal Cloacogenic Carcinoma
results.definition: An anal carcinoma arising from the transitional zone of the anal canal.

results.name: Amnesia
results.definition: Systematic and extensive loss of memory caused by organic or psychological factors. The loss may be temporary or permanent, and may involve old or recent memories.
results.glossary_definition: Loss of memory.

results.name: Hypertensive Encephalopathy
results.definition: Encephalopathy resulting from hypertension.
results.glossary_definition: Brain dysfunction or damage resulting from MALIGNANT HYPERTENSION, usually associated with a diastolic blood pressure in excess of 125 mmHg. Clinical manifestations include headache, nausea, emesis, seizures, altered mental status (in some cases progressing to COMA); PAPILLEDEMA; and RETINAL HEMORRHAGE. Focal neurologic signs may develop. Pathologically, this condition may be associated with the formation of ischemic lesions in the brain (BRAIN ISCHEMIA).

results.name: Childhood Angiosarcoma
results.definition: An angiosarcoma occurring in childhood.

results.name: Comedocarcinoma
results.definition: A high grade carcinoma characterized by the presence of comedo-type of tumor cell necrosis in which the necrotic areas are surrounded by a solid proliferation of malignant pleomorphic cells.

results.name: Myxosarcoma
results.definition: An infiltrating malignant soft tissue neoplasm characterized by the presence of immature undifferentiated cells and abundant myxoid stroma formation.
results.glossary_definition: A sarcoma, usually a liposarcoma or malignant fibrous histiocytoma, with an abundant component of myxoid tissue resembling primitive mesenchyme containing connective tissue mucin. (Stedman, 25th ed)

results.name: Extrahepatic Bile Duct Leiomyoma
match: Leiomyoma of the Extrahepatic Bile Duct
search: Leiomyoma of the Extrahepatic Bile Duct
results.definition: A benign smooth muscle neoplasm arising from an extrahepatic bile duct. It is characterized by the presence of spindle cells with cigar-shaped nuclei, interlacing fascicles, and a whorled pattern.
synonyms: Leiomyoma of the Extrahepatic Bile Duct
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Intracranial Primitive Neuroectodermal Neoplasm
results.definition: A central nervous system embryonal tumor, not otherwise specified arising from the brain.
parents: Central Nervous System Primitive Neuroectodermal Neoplasm
ancestors: Central Nervous System Primitive Neuroectodermal Neoplasm

results.name: Extrinsic Allergic Alveolitis
results.definition: An inflammatory interstitial lung disease caused by hypersensitivity reaction to inhalation or ingestion of antigens. The antigens are usually related to the patient's occupation. It can present as an acute illness with flu-like symptoms, subacute with repeated episodes of pneumonia, or chronic with dyspnea and productive cough. The majority of patients recover following the cessation of the exposure to the antigen that causes the disease. Chronic exposure may eventually progress to interstitial lung fibrosis.
results.glossary_definition: conditions in which inhalation of organic dusts results in hypersensitivity reactions at the alveolar level, associated with the production of precipitins.

results.name: Middle Ear Cholesterol Granuloma
match: Cholesterol Granuloma of the Middle Ear
search: Cholesterol Granuloma of the Middle Ear
results.definition: As accumulation of granulation tissue in the middle ear that results from the degeneration of blood and a chronic inflammatory response.
synonyms: Cholesterol Granuloma of the Middle Ear

results.name: Thymolipoma
results.definition: A well-circumscribed tumor of the thymus composed of islands of normal thymic parenchyma and mature adipose tissue. It is not clear if thymolipoma is a neoplastic or non-neoplastic lesion.

results.name: Ovarian Biphasic or Triphasic Teratoma
results.definition: A germ cell tumor that arises from the ovary and is composed of tissues that originate from two or three of the following germ layers, endoderm, ectoderm, or mesoderm.

A melanoma derived from melanocytes of the uveal tract. It is the most common primary intraocular tumor in the United States and Western Europe. Similar to melanoma of the skin, it is rare in Africa and Asia. Diagnostic procedures include ophthalmoscopic exam, fluorescein angiography and ultrasound. Treatment includes: surgical excision of the eye, iridocyclectomy and tumor resection. Recent treatments also include radiotherapy or photo coagulation. Classification of uveal melanomas recognizes four cell types within these tumors: epithelioid, intermediate, mixed cell, and spindle cell types. The spindle cell type uveal melanomas are further sub-classified as spindle cell type A and spindle cell type B.
results.glossary_definition: A rare cancer of melanocytes (cells that produce the pigment melanin) found in the eye.
results.name: Uveal Melanoma
Diaphragma Sellae Meningioma
results.definition: A meningioma that affects the diaphragma sellae.

results.name: Epithelioid Type Angiomyolipoma
results.definition: An angiomyolipoma composed exclusively or predominantly by polygonal epithelioid cells with eosinophilic cytoplasm, often associated with cytologic atypia.

results.name: Extrahepatic Bile Duct Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma
results.name_text: Extrahepatic Bile Duct Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma
match: Extrahepatic Bile Duct Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma
Bile Duct Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma
Extrahepatic Bile Duct Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma
Signet Ring Cell Bile Duct Carcinoma
Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma of Bile Duct
Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma of the Bile Duct
search: Extrahepatic Bile Duct Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma
Bile Duct Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma
Extrahepatic Bile Duct Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma
Signet Ring Cell Bile Duct Carcinoma
Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma of Bile Duct
Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma of the Bile Duct
results.definition: An adenocarcinoma that arises from the extrahepatic bile ducts. It is characterized by the presence of signet ring malignant epithelial cells.
synonyms: Bile Duct Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma
Extrahepatic Bile Duct Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma
Signet Ring Cell Bile Duct Carcinoma
Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma of Bile Duct
Signet Ring Cell Carcinoma of the Bile Duct

results.name: Frontal Convexity Meningioma
results.definition: A meningioma that affects the frontal sulcus.

results.name: Composite Ganglioneuroblastoma, Stroma-Dominant and Stroma-Poor
results.definition: A neuroblastic tumor characterized by the presence of a ganglioneuroblastoma component and the formation of Schwannian stroma which is the predominant component of the tumor volume.
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Cardiac Leiomyosarcoma
results.definition: An aggressive malignant smooth muscle neoplasm, arising from the heart. It is characterized by a proliferation of neoplastic spindle cells.

results.name: Mixed Embryonal Carcinoma and Teratoma
results.definition: A germ cell tumor characterized by the presence of an embryonal carcinoma component and a teratoma component.
results.glossary_definition: A type of germ cell cancer that usually forms in the testes (testicles).

results.name: Bernard-Soulier Syndrome
results.definition: A rare, autosomal recessive bleeding disorder characterized by deficiency or absence of the Ib/IX/V complex on the surface of platelets. It results in thrombocytopenia, prolonged bleeding time and the presence of giant platelets.

results.name: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Solid Pattern
results.name_text: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Solid Pattern
match: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Solid Pattern
Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Solid Pattern
search: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Solid Pattern
Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Solid Pattern
results.definition: A yolk sac tumor that arises from the testis and is characterized by the presence of aggregates of polygonal malignant cells with clear cytoplasm and prominent nucleoli.
synonyms: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Solid Pattern
ancestors: Malignant Testicular Non-Seminomatous Germ Cell Tumor

results.name: Rheumatic Fever
results.definition: An inflammatory disorder that follows infection with group A streptococcus. It affects the heart, joints, and subcutaneous tissues. It manifests with pericarditis, heart murmur, congestive heart failure, polyarthritis, subcutaneous nodules, and erythema marginatum. It is characterized by the formation of granulomatous lesions called Aschoff bodies usually in the heart tissue.
results.glossary_definition: An inflammatory disorder that follows infection with group A streptococcus. It may manifest with carditis, migratory polyarthritis, subcutaneous nodules, erythema marginatum, and chorea.

results.name: Pseudoglandular Squamous Cell Carcinoma
results.definition: A squamous cell carcinoma characterized by the formation of gland-like structures.

results.name: Uveomeningoencephalitic Syndrome
results.definition: A systemic inflammatory process affecting the inner ear, eyes, skin, and meninges. It is manifested with hearing disorders, panuveitis, alopecia, poliosis, vitiligo, neck stiffness, headaches, and focal neurologic signs.

results.name: Unilateral Retinoblastoma
results.definition: A retinoblastoma that only involves a single eye.

results.name: Pyloric Stenosis
results.definition: Narrowing of the pyloric lumen caused either by hypertrophy of the surrounding muscles or tissue scarring due to a chronic peptic ulcer.
results.glossary_definition: Obstruction of the pyloric canal.

results.name: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Adenoma
match: Adenoma of the Intrahepatic Bile Duct
search: Adenoma of the Intrahepatic Bile Duct
results.definition: A rare adenoma that arises from the intrahepatic biliary tree.
results.glossary_definition: A benign neoplasm arising from the intrahepatic bile duct.
synonyms: Adenoma of the Intrahepatic Bile Duct

results.name: Bladder Stone
results.definition: A concretion in the urinary bladder.
results.glossary_definition: Calculi of the urinary bladder; also known as vesical calculi or bladder stones, and cystoliths.

results.name: Colorectal Lipoma
results.definition: A rare benign adipose tissue neoplasm arising from the wall of the colon and rectum.
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Keratoacanthoma
results.definition: A dome-shaped, rapidly growing skin lesion composed of well differentiated squamous cells. It represents a proliferation of the infundibular epithelium of the hair follicle and its morphologic distinction from a well differentiated carcinoma may be difficult or impossible. Keratoacanthomas affect males more frequently than females and the majority tend to regress spontaneously. It has been suggested that keratoacanthoma represents a distinct subtype of squamous cell carcinoma of the skin.
results.glossary_definition: A rapidly growing, dome-shaped skin tumor that usually occurs on sun-exposed areas of the body, especially around the head and neck. Keratoacanthoma occurs more often in males. Although in most patients it goes away on its own, in a few patients it comes back. Rarely, it may spread to other parts of the body.
children: Multiple Self Healing Epithelioma of Ferguson-Smith

results.name: Malignant Myoepithelioma
results.definition: An infiltrating malignant tumor characterized by the presence of atypical cells with myoepithelial differentiation. Representative examples include malignant breast myoepithelioma and salivary gland myoepithelial carcinoma.
results.glossary_definition: A malignant neoplasm composed of myoepithelial cells.

results.name: Vulvar Eccrine Adenocarcinoma
results.definition: An eccrine adenocarcinoma that arises from the sweat glands in the vulva.
parents: Vulvar Adenocarcinoma of Sweat Gland Type
ancestors: Vulvar Adenocarcinoma of Sweat Gland Type

results.name: Paget Disease of the Anal Margin
results.name_text: Paget Disease of the Anal Margin
match: Paget Disease of the Anal Margin
Paget Disease of the Anal Margin
Paget's Disease of the Anal Margin
search: Paget Disease of the Anal Margin
Paget Disease of the Anal Margin
Paget's Disease of the Anal Margin
results.definition: Paget disease involving the perianal skin.
synonyms: Paget Disease of the Anal Margin
Paget's Disease of the Anal Margin

results.name: Vaginal Yolk Sac Tumor
results.definition: A rare yolk sac tumor that arises from the vagina.Patients present with abnormal vaginal bleeding or bloody discharge.

results.name: Hodgkin Lymphoma
results.definition: A lymphoma, previously known as Hodgkin's disease, characterized by the presence of large tumor cells in an abundant admixture of nonneoplastic cells. There are two distinct subtypes: nodular lymphocyte predominant Hodgkin lymphoma and classical Hodgkin lymphoma. Hodgkin lymphoma involves primarily lymph nodes.
results.glossary_definition: A cancer of the immune system that is marked by the presence of a type of cell called the Reed-Sternberg cell. The two major types of Hodgkin lymphoma are classical Hodgkin lymphoma and nodular lymphocyte-predominant Hodgkin lymphoma. Symptoms include the painless enlargement of lymph nodes, spleen, or other immune tissue. Other symptoms include fever, weight loss, fatigue, or night sweats.
children: Classic Hodgkin Lymphoma Type Post-Transplant Lymphoproliferative Disorder

results.name: Darier Disease
results.definition: An autosomal dominant inherited chronic skin disorder caused by mutations in the ATP2A2 gene. It is characterized by the development of yellow-brown keratotic skin papules in the neck, ears, forehead, chest, back and groin. It is associated with fragility of the free margins of the nails.

results.name: Lymphedema
results.definition: Excess fluid collection in tissues, causing swelling. It is the result of obstruction of lymphatic vessels or lymph nodes.
results.glossary_definition: A condition in which extra lymph fluid builds up in tissues and causes swelling. It may occur in an arm or leg if lymph vessels are blocked, damaged, or removed by surgery.

results.name: Rieger Syndrome Type 1
results.definition: A rare autosomal dominant syndrome linked to mutations in the PITX2 gene. It is characterized by abnormalities in the anterior chamber of the eye and underdevelopment of the teeth.

results.name: Uterine Ligament Neoplasm
results.definition: A benign, borderline, or malignant neoplasm that affects the uterine ligaments. Representative examples include Wolffian adnexal tumor, papillary cystadenoma, and adenocarcinoma.

results.name: Bile Duct Neoplasm
match: Intrahepatic and Extrahepatic Bile Duct Neoplasm
Intrahepatic and Extrahepatic Bile Duct Tumor
search: Intrahepatic and Extrahepatic Bile Duct Neoplasm
Intrahepatic and Extrahepatic Bile Duct Tumor
results.definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm that affects the intrahepatic or extrahepatic bile ducts. Representative examples of benign neoplasms include bile duct adenoma and extrahepatic bile duct lipoma. Representative examples of malignant neoplasms include intrahepatic and extrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma.
results.glossary_definition: Tumors or cancer of the BILE DUCTS.
synonyms: Intrahepatic and Extrahepatic Bile Duct Neoplasm
Intrahepatic and Extrahepatic Bile Duct Tumor
children: Extrahepatic Bile Duct Mucinous Cystic Neoplasm

results.name: Peritonitis
results.definition: Inflammation of the peritoneum due to infection by bacteria or fungi. Causes include liver disease, perforation of the gastrointestinal tract or biliary tract, and peritoneal dialysis. Patients usually present with abdominal pain and tenderness, fever, chills, and nausea and vomiting. It is an emergency medical condition that requires prompt medical attention and treatment.
results.glossary_definition: Inflammation of the peritoneum (tissue that lines the abdominal wall and covers most of the organs in the abdomen). Peritonitis can result from infection, injury, or certain diseases. Symptoms may include swelling of the abdomen, severe pain, and weight loss.

results.definition: A myelodysplastic/myeloproliferative neoplasm of childhood that is characterized by proliferation principally of the granulocytic and monocytic lineages. Myelomonocytic proliferation is seen in the bone marrow and the blood. The leukemic cells may infiltrate any tissue, however liver, spleen, lymph nodes, skin, and respiratory tract are the most common sites of involvement. (WHO, 2001)
results.glossary_definition: A rare form of childhood leukemia in which cancer cells often spread into tissues such as the skin, lung, and intestines.
results.name: Juvenile Myelomonocytic Leukemia
Papillary Transitional Cell Carcinoma
results.definition: A non-invasive or invasive transitional cell carcinoma characterized by a papillary growth pattern. It may occur in the bladder or the renal pelvis.

results.name: Retroperitoneal Carcinoma
results.definition: A rare carcinoma that arises from the retroperitoneal space.

results.name: Digestive System Adenoma
results.definition: A sporadic or less frequently familial neoplasm, arising from the glandular epithelium of the stomach, small intestine, biliary tract, colon, and rectum. It is a polypoid or flat circumscribed lesion. Morphologically, it is characterized by a proliferation of neoplastic glandular cells and it is associated with dysplasia. According to the growth pattern, it may be classified as tubular, villous, or tubulovillous. The dysplasia is classified as mild, moderate, or severe. The frequency of malignant transformation depends on the size of the lesion and the degree of dysplasia. Larger adenomas with severe dysplastic changes (sometimes called carcinoma in situ) carry a higher risk of progressing to invasive adenocarcinoma. Gastrointestinal adenomas may present as solitary or multifocal lesions. Familial adenomas tend to be multifocal and carry a higher risk of malignant transformation.

results.name: Giant Cell Tumor
results.definition: A benign, intermediate, or malignant tumor that arises from the bone or soft tissue. It is characterized by the presence of multinucleated osteoclast-like giant cells.
results.glossary_definition: A neoplasm of bone comprised of giant cells (osteoclast-like) and mononuclear cells, for which the malignancy status has not been established.
children: Osteoclastic Giant Cell-Rich Tumor of Bone

results.name: Adult Central Nervous System Teratoma
match: Teratoma of Adult Central Nervous System
Teratoma of the Adult Central Nervous System
search: Teratoma of Adult Central Nervous System
Teratoma of the Adult Central Nervous System
results.definition: A mature or immature teratoma affecting the central nervous system and occurring in adults.
synonyms: Teratoma of Adult Central Nervous System
Teratoma of the Adult Central Nervous System
parents: Central Nervous System Adult Germ Cell Tumor
ancestors: Central Nervous System Adult Germ Cell Tumor
Central Nervous System Germ Cell Tumor
children: Adult Central Nervous System Mature Teratoma

results.name: Embryonal Rhabdomyosarcoma
results.definition: A poorly circumscribed morphologic variant of rhabdomyosarcoma. It is characterized by the presence of primitive skeletal muscle differentiation in any stage of myogenesis.
results.glossary_definition: A soft tissue tumor that is most common in infants and young children. It begins in muscles, usually in the head, neck, or genitourinary tract.

results.name: Childhood Central Nervous System Mature Teratoma
results.name_text: Childhood Central Nervous System Mature Teratoma
match: Childhood Central Nervous System Mature Teratoma
Childhood Central Nervous System Mature Teratoma
search: Childhood Central Nervous System Mature Teratoma
Childhood Central Nervous System Mature Teratoma
results.definition: A mature teratoma that arises from the central nervous system during childhood.
synonyms: Childhood Central Nervous System Mature Teratoma
ancestors: Central Nervous System Germ Cell Tumor

results.name: Favism
results.definition: A condition associated with glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase deficiency, which is characterized by hemolysis.
results.glossary_definition: Hemolytic anemia due to the ingestion of fava beans or after inhalation of pollen from the Vicia fava plant by persons with glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase deficient erythrocytes.

results.name: Hemoglobin D Disease
results.definition: A condition characterized by the presence of a variant of normal hemoglobin (hemoglobin D), which is caused by mutation(s) in the gene encoding the beta subunit of the hemoglobin molecule.

results.name: Achromatopsia
results.definition: An autosomal recessive genetic disorder affecting the cone cells of the eye. It may be complete, in which the individual can only perceive black, white, or shades or gray, or incomplete, in which the individual has a residual amount of color vision.

results.name: Cardiac Sarcoma
results.definition: A malignant soft tissue neoplasm that arises from the heart. The majority of cases are angiosarcomas.
results.glossary_definition: A rare cancer that develops in tissues of the heart.

results.name: Glycine Encephalopathy
results.definition: An autosomal recessive metabolic disorder caused by mutations in the AMT and GLDC genes. It is characterized by abnormal accumulation of glycine in the brain and other tissues. Signs and symptoms include lethargy, feeding difficulties, hypotonia, intellectual deformities, and seizures.

results.name: Metastatic Carcinoma in the Bone
results.definition: A carcinoma that has spread to the bone from another, primary anatomic site. Bone is one of the most frequent sites of metastatic carcinoma. Common sites of origin include lung, breast, and prostate.
ancestors: Malignant Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Peritoneal Mesothelioma
results.definition: A benign or malignant mesothelial neoplasm that arises from the peritoneum.

results.name: Malignant Breast Myoepithelioma
results.definition: An invasive malignant tumor that arises from the breast. It is characterized by the presence of spindle-shaped myoepithelial cells. Mitoses are present. Rarely, local recurrences and distant metastases have been reported.

results.name: Endocarditis
results.definition: Inflammation of the endocardium.
results.glossary_definition: Inflammation of the endocardium.

results.name: Epidermolytic Acanthoma
results.definition: A benign epithelial verrucous lesion of the skin. Morphologically, it is characterized by the presence of epidermolytic hyperkeratosis and papillomatosis.

results.name: Atypical Neurofibroma
results.definition: A neurofibroma characterized by the presence of cellular pleomorphism.
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Lymphocytic Colitis
results.definition: Microscopic colitis characterized by the accumulation of lymphocytes in the colonic epithelium and lamina propria. Patients present with chronic watery diarrhea. Colonoscopy reveals normal colonic mucosa. The diagnosis is made with the microscopic examination of the colonic biopsy samples.

results.name: Granulomatous Arteritis
results.definition: Inflammation of the arteries that is characterized by the presence of granulomas.

results.name: Partial Motor Seizure
results.definition: A simple partial seizure consisting of clonus or spasm of a muscle or muscle group; it may be single or in a continuous and repetitive series or may spread to adjacent muscles.
results.glossary_definition: A simple partial seizure consisting of clonus or spasm of a muscle or muscle group; it may be single or in a continuous and repetitive series or may spread to adjacent muscles.

results.name: Inverted Urothelial Papilloma
results.definition: An endophytic lesion in the urinary tract which shares several morphologic features with urothelial papilloma. This lesion may recur after complete excision. Transitional cell carcinomas may arise within inverted urothelial papillomas.

results.name: Female Orgasmic Disorder
results.definition: A sexual disorder in which a woman fails to achieve orgasm during sexual intercourse.

results.name: Noonan Syndrome 1
results.definition: Noonan syndrome caused by mutations in the PTPN11 gene.

results.name: Verruca Vulgaris
results.definition: A wart caused by human papillomavirus. It can appear anywhere on the skin.

results.name: Pulmonary Emphysema
results.definition: A subcategory of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). It occurs in people who smoke and suffer from chronic bronchitis. It is characterized by inflation of the alveoli, alveolar wall damage, and reduction in the number of alveoli, resulting in difficulty breathing.
results.glossary_definition: Pulmonary emphysema is a disorder affecting the alveoli (tiny air sacs) of the lungs. The transfer of oxygen and carbon dioxide in the lungs takes place in the walls of the alveoli. In emphysema, the alveoli become abnormally inflated, damaging their walls and making it harder to breathe. People who smoke or have chronic bronchitis have an increased risk of emphysema.

results.name: Skin Papilloma
results.definition: A benign papillary neoplastic growth on the skin composed of epithelial cells and a fibrous stalk. It usually develops in the eyelid, axilla, neck, upper chest, and groin.
results.glossary_definition: small pendulous outgrowth of the skin; in middle life, it usually occurs on the neck in pedunculated seborrheic keratosis.

results.name: Dacryoadenitis
results.definition: Inflammation and enlargement of the lacrimal gland.

results.name: Osgood-Schlatter's Disease
results.definition: Osteochondrosis of the growth plate near the tibial tuberosity.

results.name: Periodontal Disorder
results.definition: An inflammatory process of the gingival tissues and/or periodontal membrane of the teeth, resulting in an abnormally deep gingival sulcus, possibly producing periodontal pockets and loss of alveolar bone support.
results.glossary_definition: A disorder in the gingival tissue around the teeth.

results.name: Measles
results.definition: A highly contagious viral infection caused by the measles virus. Symptoms appear 8-12 days after exposure and include a rash, cough, fever and muscle pains that can last 4-7 days. Measles vaccines are available to provide prophylaxis, usually combined with mumps and rubella vaccines (MMR).

results.name: Cervical Leukoplakia
results.definition: The presence of whitish patches on the mucosal surface of the cervix. Histologic examination reveals hyperkeratosis. In a minority of cases, underlying dysplasia or carcinoma in situ is present.

results.name: Hepatobiliary Neoplasm
results.definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm that affects the liver parenchyma, bile ducts, and gallbladder. Representative examples of benign neoplasms include hepatocellular adenoma, bile duct adenoma, and gallbladder lipoma. Representative examples of malignant neoplasms include hepatocellular carcinoma, intrahepatic and extrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma, and gallbladder carcinoma.
children: Liver and Intrahepatic Bile Duct Neoplasm

results.name: Acantholytic Squamous Cell Skin Carcinoma
match: Acantholytic Squamous Cell Carcinoma of Skin
Acantholytic Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Skin
search: Acantholytic Squamous Cell Carcinoma of Skin
Acantholytic Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Skin
results.definition: A histologic variant of squamous cell carcinoma that arises from the skin. It is characterized by loosening of the intercellular bridges between the malignant cells which results in acantholysis.
synonyms: Acantholytic Squamous Cell Carcinoma of Skin
Acantholytic Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Skin

results.name: Bone Paget Disease
results.definition: A disease of bone that initially results in the excessive resorption of bone (by osteoclasts) followed by the replacement of normal bone marrow with vascular and fibrous tissue.
results.glossary_definition: A chronic condition in which both the breakdown and regrowth of bone are increased. Paget disease of bone occurs most frequently in the pelvic and leg bones, skull, and lower spine. It is most common in older individuals, and may lead to bone pain, deformities, and fractures.

results.name: Lung Adenocarcinoma
results.definition: A carcinoma that arises from the lung and is characterized by the presence of malignant glandular epithelial cells. There is a male predilection with a male to female ratio of 2:1. Usually lung adenocarcinoma is asymptomatic and is identified through screening studies or as an incidental radiologic finding. If clinical symptoms are present they include shortness of breath, cough, hemoptysis, chest pain, and fever. Tobacco smoke is a known risk factor.

results.name: Orchitis
results.definition: Inflammation of one or both testes due to viral or bacterial infections. Signs and symptoms include enlargement or tenderness of the affected testis, inguinal lymphadenopathy, blood in the semen, and pain during urination, intercourse, or ejaculation.
results.glossary_definition: Inflammation of one or both testicles.

results.name: Ovarian Stromal Hyperthecosis
results.definition: A non-neoplastic disorder that usually affects postmenopausal women. It is characterized by the leuteinization of ovarian stromal cells. The ovaries are bilaterally involved and enlarged. When it affects women in reproductive age, it causes virilization, high blood pressure, and increased insulin levels.

results.name: Yolk Sac Tumor
results.definition: A non-seminomatous malignant germ cell tumor composed of primitive germ cells. It is the most common malignant germ cell tumor in the pediatric population. It occurs in the infant testis, ovary, sacrococcygeal region, vagina, uterus, prostate, abdomen, liver, retroperitoneum, thorax, and pineal/third ventricle. The tumor mimics the yolk sac of the embryo and produces alpha-fetoprotein (AFP). Treatment includes: surgical resection, radiation, and chemotherapy. This tumor is very responsive to chemotherapy regimens that include cisplatinum.
results.glossary_definition: An unusual and aggressive tumor of germ-cell origin that reproduces the extraembryonic structures of the early embryo. It is the most common malignant germ cell tumor found in children. It is characterized by a labyrinthine glandular pattern of flat epithelial cells and rounded papillary processes with a central capillary (Schiller-Duval body). The tumor is rarely bilateral. Before the use of combination chemotherapy, the tumor was almost invariably fatal. (From DeVita Jr et al., Cancer: Principles & Practice of Oncology, 3d ed, p1189)
children: Central Nervous System Yolk Sac Tumor

results.name: Nicotine Dependence
results.definition: Physical and psychological dependence on nicotine.

results.name: Hereditary Retinal Dystrophy
results.definition: An inherited form of retinal dystrophy.

results.name: Childhood Medulloblastoma
results.definition: A medulloblastoma occurring in children.

results.name: Laryngeal Neoplasm
results.definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm involving the larynx.
results.glossary_definition: Cancers or tumors of the LARYNX or any of its parts: the GLOTTIS, EPIGLOTTIS, LARYNGEAL CARTILAGES, LARYNGEAL MUSCLES, and VOCAL CORDS.

results.name: Arteriosclerotic Cardiovascular Disease
results.definition: Cardiovascular disease resulting from arteriosclerosis.

results.name: Brain Hemangioma
results.definition: A hemangioma arising from the brain.
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.definition: One of the most common malignant tumors afflicting men. The majority of carcinomas arise in the peripheral zone and a minority occur in the central or the transitional zone of the prostate gland. Grossly, prostatic carcinomas appear as ill-defined yellow areas of discoloration in the prostate gland lobes. Adenocarcinomas represent the overwhelming majority of prostatic carcinomas. Prostatic-specific antigen (PSA) serum test is widely used as a screening test for the early detection of prostatic carcinoma. Treatment options include radical prostatectomy, radiation therapy, androgen ablation and cryotherapy. Watchful waiting or surveillance alone is an option for older patients with low-grade or low-stage disease.
results.glossary_definition: Cancer that forms in tissues of the prostate (a gland in the male reproductive system found below the bladder and in front of the rectum). Prostate cancer usually occurs in older men.
results.name: Prostate Carcinoma
Rete Testis Adenocarcinoma
results.definition: A rare adenocarcinoma that arises from the rete testis. It is usually manifested with a scrotal mass or lumbar pain.

results.name: Hereditary Breast and Ovarian Cancer Syndrome
results.name_text: Hereditary Breast and Ovarian Cancer Syndrome
match: Hereditary Breast and Ovarian Cancer Syndrome
Familial Breast and Ovarian Cancer Syndrome
Hereditary Breast and Ovarian Cancer Syndrome
search: Hereditary Breast and Ovarian Cancer Syndrome
Familial Breast and Ovarian Cancer Syndrome
Hereditary Breast and Ovarian Cancer Syndrome
results.definition: An autosomal dominant inherited syndrome caused by mutations in the BRCA1 or BRCA2 genes. Patients are at high risk of developing breast cancer, particularly before the age of fifty, high risk of developing a second primary breast cancer, and high risk of developing both breast and ovarian cancer.
synonyms: Familial Breast and Ovarian Cancer Syndrome
Hereditary Breast and Ovarian Cancer Syndrome

results.name: Acute Infective Polyneuritis
results.definition: An acute inflammatory process affecting the peripheral nervous system and nerve roots. It results in demyelination. It is often caused by an acute viral or bacterial infection.
parents: Autoimmune Disease Of Peripheral Nervous System
ancestors: Autoimmune Disease Of Peripheral Nervous System

results.name: Nephritis
results.definition: Inflammation of renal tissue.

results.name: Lung Leiomyoma
results.definition: A benign smooth muscle neoplasm arising from the lung. It is characterized by the presence of spindle cells with cigar-shaped nuclei, interlacing fascicles, and a whorled pattern.

results.name: Asbestosis
results.definition: A lung disorder caused by inhalation of asbestos fibers. It results in fibrosis of the lung parenchyma. Signs and symptoms include coughing, shortness of breath and chest pain.
results.glossary_definition: A lung disease caused by breathing in particles of asbestos (a group of minerals that take the form of tiny fibers). Symptoms include coughing, trouble breathing, and chest pain caused by scarring and permanent damage to lung tissue. Asbestosis increases the risk of lung cancer and malignant mesothelioma (cancer found in the lining of the lungs, chest, or abdomen).

results.name: Duodenal Ulcer
results.definition: An ulcer in the duodenal wall.
results.glossary_definition: A peptic ulcer situated in the duodenum. (Dorland, 28th ed)

results.name: Nesidioblastosis
results.definition: A sporadic or inherited disorder characterized by the focal or diffuse proliferation of the cells of the islets of Langerhans in the pancreas. It results in hyperinsulinemia and hypoglycemia.

results.name: Pancreatic Insulin-Producing Neuroendocrine Tumor
match: Beta Cell Tumor of the Pancreas
Insulin-Producing Tumor of the Islet Cells
search: Beta Cell Tumor of the Pancreas
Insulin-Producing Tumor of the Islet Cells
results.definition: An insulin-producing neuroendocrine tumor arising from the beta cells of the pancreas. It may or may not be associated with inappropriate secretion of insulin and an associated clinical syndrome.
results.glossary_definition: An abnormal mass that grows in the beta cells of the pancreas that make insulin. Beta cell neoplasms are usually benign (not cancer). They secrete insulin and are the most common cause of low blood sugar caused by having too much insulin in the body.
synonyms: Beta Cell Tumor of the Pancreas
Insulin-Producing Tumor of the Islet Cells

results.name: Stomach Disorder
results.definition: A non-neoplastic or neoplastic disorder that affects the stomach. Representative examples of non-neoplastic disorders include gastritis and gastric ulcer. Representative examples of neoplastic disorders include adenomas, carcinomas, and lymphomas.

results.name: Diabetic Vascular Disorder
results.definition: Vascular disorders resulting from diabetes mellitus.

results.name: Biphasic Synovial Sarcoma
results.definition: A synovial sarcoma characterized by the presence of both an epithelial and a spindle cell component.

results.name: Dermatofibrosarcoma Protuberans
results.definition: A low grade fibroblastic neoplasm presenting as a nodular cutaneous mass, most often on the trunk and the proximal extremities. The tumor diffusely infiltrates the dermis and the subcutaneous tissues. It is considered a locally aggressive neoplasm, which often recurs but rarely metastasizes.
results.glossary_definition: A type of tumor that begins as a hard nodule and grows slowly. These tumors are usually found in the dermis (the inner layer of the two main layers of tissue that make up the skin) of the limbs or trunk of the body. They can grow into surrounding tissue but do not spread to other parts of the body. These tumors are related to giant cell fibroblastomas.

results.name: Reproductive System Neoplasm
results.definition: A benign or malignant, primary or metastatic neoplasm affecting the male and female reproductive system.

results.name: Pacinian Neurofibroma
results.definition: A neurofibroma characterized by the presence of structures which resemble Vater-Pacini corpuscles.
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Skull Neoplasm
results.definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm that affects the bones and structures of the skull.
results.glossary_definition: Neoplasms of the bony part of the skull.

results.name: Holocarboxylase Synthetase Deficiency
results.definition: A rare autosomal recessive inherited disorder caused by mutations in the HLCS gene. It is characterized by deficiency of the enzyme holocarboxylase synthetase which facilitates the effective use of the vitamin biotin in the body. Signs and symptoms appear early in life and include breathing difficulties, feeding difficulties, alopecia, skin rash, and lethargy. Lifelong administration of biotin supplements is required. If it is not treated properly, it may lead to developmental delays, seizures, and coma.

results.name: Autoimmune Lymphoproliferative Syndrome
results.definition: An autoimmune hematologic disorder characterized by autoimmune hemolytic anemia, thrombocytopenia, lymphadenopathy, hepatomegaly and splenomegaly. Patients are at an increased risk of developing Hodgkin and non-Hodgkin lymphomas.

results.name: Cerebral Primitive Neuroectodermal Tumor
match: Primitive Neuroectodermal Neoplasm of Cerebral Hemispheres
Primitive Neuroectodermal Neoplasm of the Cerebral Hemispheres
Primitive Neuroectodermal Neoplasm of the Cerebrum
Primitive Neuroectodermal Tumor of Cerebral Hemispheres
Primitive Neuroectodermal Tumor of the Cerebral Hemispheres
Primitive Neuroectodermal Tumor of the Cerebrum
search: Primitive Neuroectodermal Neoplasm of Cerebral Hemispheres
Primitive Neuroectodermal Neoplasm of the Cerebral Hemispheres
Primitive Neuroectodermal Neoplasm of the Cerebrum
Primitive Neuroectodermal Tumor of Cerebral Hemispheres
Primitive Neuroectodermal Tumor of the Cerebral Hemispheres
Primitive Neuroectodermal Tumor of the Cerebrum
results.definition: A central nervous system embryonal tumor, not otherwise specified arising from the cerebral hemispheres.
synonyms: Primitive Neuroectodermal Neoplasm of Cerebral Hemispheres
Primitive Neuroectodermal Neoplasm of the Cerebral Hemispheres
Primitive Neuroectodermal Neoplasm of the Cerebrum
Primitive Neuroectodermal Tumor of Cerebral Hemispheres
Primitive Neuroectodermal Tumor of the Cerebral Hemispheres
Primitive Neuroectodermal Tumor of the Cerebrum

results.name: Kidney Hemangiopericytoma
results.definition: A hemangiopericytoma arising from the kidney.

results.name: Orbit Neoplasm
results.definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm that affects the orbit.
results.glossary_definition: Neoplasms of the bony orbit and contents except the eyeball.
ancestors: Malignant Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Sternal Lymphoma
results.definition: A rare lymphoma that arises from the bone or soft tissue of the sternum.
ancestors: Malignant Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Posterolateral Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding
results.name_text: Posterolateral Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding
match: Posterolateral Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding
Posterolateral Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding
Posterolateral Myocardial Infarction by EKG Finding
search: Posterolateral Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding
Posterolateral Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding
Posterolateral Myocardial Infarction by EKG Finding
results.definition: An electrocardiographic finding of an injury in leads corresponding to the anatomic region of the posterolateral wall of the heart.
synonyms: Posterolateral Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding
Posterolateral Myocardial Infarction by EKG Finding

results.name: Spondylolisthesis
results.definition: A condition in which there is forward displacement of a vertebral bone over the on below it.
results.glossary_definition: Forward displacement of one vertebra over another.

results.name: Duodenal Gastrin-Producing Neuroendocrine Tumor
match: Gastrin Producing Tumor of the Duodenum
search: Gastrin Producing Tumor of the Duodenum
results.definition: A gastrin-producing neuroendocrine tumor that arises from the duodenum. It is characterized by the presence of uniform cells that form pseudorosettes. The neoplastic cells have uniform nuclei and small amount of eosinophilic cytoplasm.
synonyms: Gastrin Producing Tumor of the Duodenum

results.name: Retinoschisis
results.definition: An inherited or acquired disorder characterized by splitting of the retina into two layers. It results in loss of vision.

results.name: Leiomyosarcoma of Central Nervous System
match: Leiomyosarcoma of the Central Nervous System
search: Leiomyosarcoma of the Central Nervous System
results.definition: An aggressive malignant smooth muscle neoplasm, arising from the central nervous system. It is characterized by a proliferation of neoplastic spindle cells.
synonyms: Leiomyosarcoma of the Central Nervous System
parents: Central Nervous System Mesenchymal Non-meningothelial Tumor
ancestors: Central Nervous System Mesenchymal Non-meningothelial Tumor

results.name: Skin Clear Cell Basal Cell Carcinoma
results.name_text: Skin Clear Cell Basal Cell Carcinoma
match: Skin Clear Cell Basal Cell Carcinoma
Skin Clear Cell Basal Cell Carcinoma
search: Skin Clear Cell Basal Cell Carcinoma
Skin Clear Cell Basal Cell Carcinoma
results.definition: A morphologic variant of basal cell carcinoma characterized by the presence of clear cells.
synonyms: Skin Clear Cell Basal Cell Carcinoma

results.name: Lipomatosis
results.definition: A neoplastic process characterized by diffuse overgrowth of mature adipose tissue.
parents: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Urethral Adenocarcinoma
results.definition: An adenocarcinoma that arises from the male or female urethra.

results.name: Placenta Accreta
results.definition: The clinical condition in which any part of the placenta invades and is inseparable from the uterine wall. (reVITALize)
results.glossary_definition: The clinical condition in which any part of the placenta invades and is inseparable from the uterine wall. [verbatim from reVITALize]

results.name: Ethmoid Sinus Inverted Papilloma
match: Inverted Papilloma of the Ethmoid Sinus
search: Inverted Papilloma of the Ethmoid Sinus
results.definition: A benign neoplasm that arises from the ciliated respiratory mucosa that lines the ethmoid sinus. It results from the invagination and proliferation of epithelial cells in the underlying stroma.
synonyms: Inverted Papilloma of the Ethmoid Sinus

results.name: Viral Hepatitis
results.definition: An acute or chronic inflammation of the liver parenchyma caused by viruses. Representative examples include hepatitis A, B, and C, cytomegalovirus hepatitis, and herpes simplex hepatitis.
results.glossary_definition: A disorder characterized by a viral pathologic process involving the liver parenchyma.

results.name: Sarcomatoid Renal Cell Carcinoma
match: Renal cell carcinoma with sarcomatoid features
search: Renal cell carcinoma with sarcomatoid features
results.definition: A high grade carcinoma of the kidney. It is not a distinct clinicopathological entity and includes a diverse group of renal cell carcinomas which have been transformed from a lower to a higher grade.
synonyms: Renal cell carcinoma with sarcomatoid features

results.name: American Cutaneous Leishmaniasis
results.definition: The most common form of leishmaniasis that is transmitted through the bite of female phlebotomine sand flies or after exposure to leishmania parasites. It is characterized by skin lesions at the site of insect bite which typically develop within weeks or months after exposure. The lesions typically progress from small papules to open sores with raised borders and central ulcers which can be covered with scales or crust.

results.name: Breast Extraskeletal Osteosarcoma
results.definition: An osteosarcoma arising from the breast tissue.

results.name: Nonossifying Fibromyxoid Tumor
results.definition: A rare soft tissue tumor of uncertain lineage characterized by the presence of neoplastic spindle to round cells forming cords in a fibromyxoid stroma. Metaplastic bone formation is not present.

results.name: Childhood Supratentorial Ependymoma
results.definition: An ependymoma that arises from the supratentorial region of the brain and occurs during childhood.
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Alpha-1 Antitrypsin Deficiency
results.definition: A genetic disorder characterized by decreased alpha-1 antitrypsin activity in the lungs and blood and deposition of alpha-1 antitrypsin protein in the hepatocytes. These abnormalities result from defective production of alpha-1 antitrypsin and lead to the development of emphysema, cirrhosis, and liver failure.

results.name: MELAS Syndrome
results.definition: A rare progressive neurodegenerative disorder characterized by mitochondrial myopathy, encephalopathy, lactic acidosis, and stroke-like episodes.

results.name: Angelman Syndrome
results.definition: A genetic syndrome characterized by mental retardation, speech impairment, microcephaly, ataxia, and seizures. The majority of cases result from deletions on the long arm of chromosome 15. A minority of cases result from mutations in the UBE3A gene.

results.name: Psychogenic Vaginismus
results.definition: Involuntary spasm of the outer muscles of the vagina during penetration that results from a psychological cause.

results.name: Esophageal Squamous Papilloma
match: Squamous Cell Papilloma of the Esophagus
search: Squamous Cell Papilloma of the Esophagus
results.definition: A rare neoplasm arising from the distal third of the esophagus. Morphologically, it is characterized by the presence of fibrovascular cores covered by mature stratified squamous epithelium. Progression to squamous cell carcinoma is extremely rare.
synonyms: Squamous Cell Papilloma of the Esophagus

results.name: Pulpitis
results.definition: Inflammation of the dental pulp.

results.name: Secretory Meningioma
results.definition: A WHO grade I meningioma characterized by the presence of epithelial differentiation and numerous intracellular PAS positive bodies that are rich in glycogen.

results.name: Retinal Arterial Branch Occlusion
results.definition: An occlusion of a branch of the retinal artery.

results.name: Early Yaws
results.definition: Early yaws includes primary and secondary stages of yaws, endemic tropical treponemal nonvenereal infection: development of initial lesion at inoculation site followed by widespread dissemination of treponemes and generalized secondary granulomatous lesions that may relapse repeatedly.

results.name: Schizoaffective Disorder
results.definition: A disorder in which the individual suffers from both symptoms that qualify as schizophrenia and symptoms that qualify as a mood disorder (e.g., depression or bipolar disorder) for a substantial portion (but not all) of the active period of the illness; for the remainder of the active period of the illness, the individual suffers from delusions or hallucinations in the absence of prominent mood symptoms.

results.name: Congenital Syphilis
results.definition: A life-threatening bacterial infection of the newborn caused by Treponema pallidum. It is transmitted to the infant from a mother with syphilis through the placenta during pregnancy. Signs and symptoms include irritability, fever, failure to thrive, saddle nose, cutaneous rash, and pneumonia.

results.name: Bladder Schistosomiasis
results.definition: A bladder infection that occurs as a manifetation of a systemic infection with one or more species of the parasitic worms of the Schistosoma type; this can progress to bladder cancer in time.
results.glossary_definition: Schistosomiasis caused by SCHISTOSOMA HAEMATOBIUM. It is endemic in Africa and parts of the Middle East, and affects the urinary tract.

results.name: Fibroma
results.definition: A non-metastasizing neoplasm arising from the fibrous tissue. It is characterized by the presence of spindle-shaped fibroblasts.
results.glossary_definition: A benign tumor of fibrous or fully developed connective tissue.

results.name: Nodular Melanoma
match: Nodular Malignant Melanoma of the Skin
search: Nodular Malignant Melanoma of the Skin
results.definition: An aggressive form of melanoma, frequently metastasizing to the lymph nodes. It presents as a papular or nodular raised skin lesion. It comprises approximately 10-15% of melanomas. Morphologically, it often displays an epithelioid appearance.
synonyms: Nodular Malignant Melanoma of the Skin

results.name: Respiratory Failure
results.definition: The significant impairment of gas exchange within the lungs resulting in hypoxia, hypercarbia, or both, to the extent that organ tissue perfusion is severely compromised. Causes include chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, asthma, emphysema, acute respiratory distress syndrome, pneumonia, pulmonary edema, pneumothorax, and congestive heart failure. Treatment requires intubation and mechanical ventilation until the time the lungs recover sufficient function.
results.glossary_definition: The significant impairment of gas exchange resulting in hypoxia and/or hypercarbia, to the extent that tissue oxygenation is severely compromised.

results.name: Treacher Collins Syndrome
results.definition: A rare autosomal dominant syndrome caused by mutations in the TCOF1 gene. Its characteristics include underdevelopment of the facial bones, small jaw and chin, absent or small ears, defects in the middle ear resulting in hearing loss, and downward sloping palpebral fissures.

results.name: Chronic Polyneuropathy
results.definition: Polyneuropathy that is persistent or long-standing in nature.

results.name: Central Nervous System Teratoma
match: Teratoma of the Central Nervous System
search: Teratoma of the Central Nervous System
results.definition: A mature or immature teratoma that affects the central nervous system.
synonyms: Teratoma of the Central Nervous System
parents: Central Nervous System Germ Cell Tumor
ancestors: Central Nervous System Germ Cell Tumor
children: Central Nervous System Teratoma with Malignant Transformation

results.name: Vasculitis
results.definition: An inflammatory process involving the wall of the vessels (large, medium, or small-sized vessels). The inflammatory process may cause necrosis or formation of granulomas in the vascular wall. It may be the result of an autoimmune disorder, infection, or malignancy. Representative examples include polyarteritis nodosa, temporal arteritis, Wegener granulomatosis, Kawasaki disease, Takayasu arteritis, and Henoch-Schonlein purpura.
results.glossary_definition: Inflammation of a blood vessel.

results.name: Lissencephaly
results.definition: A rare genetic brain malformation characterized by smooth folds and grooves in the brain. There are approximately 20 different types of lissencephaly that are identified by various symptoms.
results.glossary_definition: A brain malformation characterized by smooth folds and grooves in the brain.

results.name: Adenine Phosphoribosyltransferase Deficiency
results.definition: An inherited condition caused by mutations in the APRT gene that affects the kidneys and urinary tract. The most common feature of this condition is recurrent kidney stones.

results.name: Acute Disseminated Encephalomyelitis
results.definition: An inflammatory process affecting the central nervous system. It is characterized by perivascular demyelination. Symptoms usually follow an acute viral infection or immunization and include fever, confusion, somnolence and involuntary movements. It may lead to coma and death.
results.glossary_definition: Transitory inflammation of the brain and spinal cord associated with demyelination with or without neuronal damage.

results.name: Pancreatic Mucinous-Cystic Neoplasm
results.definition: A non-invasive or invasive cystic epithelial neoplasm that affects almost exclusively females. It is characterized by the presence of columnar mucin-producing epithelial cells and ovarian-type stroma formation.
children: Pancreatic Mucinous-Cystic Neoplasm with an Associated Invasive Carcinoma

results.name: Childhood Cerebral Ependymoma
results.definition: A cerebral ependymoma that occurs during childhood.
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Peritoneal Malignant Mesothelioma
results.definition: An aggressive malignant mesothelioma that arises from the peritoneum. Patients usually present with abdominal pain and ascites.

results.name: Middle Ear Polyp
results.definition: A benign polypoid growth in the middle ear.

results.name: Cecum Adenocarcinoma
results.definition: An adenocarcinoma arising from the cecum. It is more frequently seen in populations with a Western type diet and in patients with a history of chronic inflammatory bowel disease. Histologic variants include mucinous adenocarcinoma, signet ring cell carcinoma, medullary carcinoma, serrated adenocarcinoma, cribriform comedo-type adenocarcinoma, and micropapillary adenocarcinoma.

results.name: Thymic Squamous Cell Carcinoma
match: Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Thymus
search: Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Thymus
results.definition: A rare primary thymic carcinoma, characterized by the presence of keratinizing or non-keratinizing malignant squamous cells. Approximately 10-20% of cases occur in combination with thymoma. The prognosis depends on the tumor stage and the degree of cellular differentiation.
synonyms: Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Thymus

results.name: Achondrogenesis
results.definition: A rare group of disorders characterized by defective development of bones and cartilage.

results.name: Complex Regional Pain Syndrome I
results.definition: A neurologic condition characterized by burning pain, tenderness, swelling, and changes in the skin color and temperature of a body part or extremity that has no identifiable nerve injury; most pediatric patients present with this form.
results.glossary_definition: A neurologic condition characterized by burning pain, tenderness, swelling, and changes in the skin color and temperature of a body part or extremity that has no identifiable nerve injury; most pediatric patients present with this form.

results.name: Myocarditis
results.definition: Inflammation of the muscle tissue of the heart.
results.glossary_definition: Inflammation of the myocardium.

results.name: Mitochondrial Myopathy
results.definition: Myopathy caused by mitochondrial abnormalities.

results.name: Loeys-Dietz Syndrome
results.definition: A rare autosomal dominant syndrome caused by mutations in the TGFBR1 or TGFBR2 genes. It is characterized by vascular abnormalities including aortic and arterial aneurysms, aortic dissection, and tortuosity of the arteries. Other findings include scoliosis, long fingers, and joint hypermobility. Patients with TGFBR1 gene mutations also exhibit hypertelorism, bifid uvula, and early fusion of the skull bones.

results.name: Aspergillosis
results.definition: An infection that is caused by Aspergillus.
results.glossary_definition: An infectious fungal disease that occurs most often in the skin, ears, nasal sinuses, and lungs of people with suppressed immune systems.

results.definition: A variant of mastocytosis characterized by multifocal, dense infiltrates of mast cells (15 or more mast cells in aggregates) detected in the bone marrow and/or other extracutaneous sites. (WHO, 2001) -- 2003
results.glossary_definition: A rare disease in which too many mast cells (a type of immune system cell) are found in the skin, bones, joints, lymph nodes, liver, spleen, and gastrointestinal tract. Mast cells give off chemicals such as histamine that can cause flushing (a hot, red face), itching, abdominal cramps, muscle pain, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, low blood pressure, and shock.
results.name: Systemic Mastocytosis
Cognitive Disorder
results.definition: A category of psychiatric disorders which are characterized by a deficit in cognition or memory.

results.name: Cervical Mucinous Adenocarcinoma, Endocervical Type
results.definition: A cervical mucinous adenocarcinoma characterized by the presence of malignant glandular cells that resemble those of the endocervix.

results.name: Intraductal Papillary Breast Neoplasm
results.definition: A benign or malignant papillary neoplasm that arises anywhere in the ductal system of the breast. It is characterized by fibrovascular structures lined by epithelial proliferations. This category includes intraductal papilloma and intraductal papillary carcinoma.

results.name: Leptospirosis
results.definition: A contagious bacterial infection caused by spirochetes of the genus Leptospira. Humans are infected by contact with water and soil which have been contaminated with animal waste products. The signs and symptoms include an initial flu-like phase, followed by a second phase in which patients may develop meningitis, liver failure and renal failure.

results.name: Ovarian Serous Surface Papillary Adenocarcinoma
match: Serous Surface Papillary Carcinoma of Ovary
Serous Surface Papillary Carcinoma of the Ovary
search: Serous Surface Papillary Carcinoma of Ovary
Serous Surface Papillary Carcinoma of the Ovary
results.definition: A serous adenocarcinoma that arises from the ovary and is characterized by the presence of a papillary architectural pattern.
synonyms: Serous Surface Papillary Carcinoma of Ovary
Serous Surface Papillary Carcinoma of the Ovary

results.name: Hobnail Hemangioma
results.definition: A hemangioma characterized by the presence of hobnail endothelial cells.
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Fallopian Tube Papilloma
results.definition: A benign epithelial neoplasm that arises from the fallopian tube. It is characterized by the presence of fibrovascular stalks lined by serous epithelial cells.

results.name: Laryngeal Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma
match: Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma of the Larynx
search: Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma of the Larynx
results.definition: A rare adenoid cystic carcinoma of the larynx. It usually arises from the supraglottic or subglottic area. It is characterized by slow progression and late distant metastases.
synonyms: Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma of the Larynx

results.name: Epithelial-Myoepithelial Carcinoma
results.definition: A malignant neoplasm which occurs mostly in the major salivary glands (most frequently in the parotid gland), but also in the minor salivary glands of the oral mucosa and the tracheobronchial tree. It is characterized by the presence of ductal structures which are lined by an inner layer of cuboidal epithelial-type cells and an outer layer of myoepithelial cells with clear or eosinophilic cytoplasm.

results.name: Stickler Syndrome
results.definition: A rare autosomal dominant syndrome caused by mutations in the COL11A1, COL11A2, and COL2A1 genes which affect the production of type II and XI collagen. It is characterized by a range of signs and symptoms including cleft palate, large tongue, small lower jaw, hearing loss, myopia, glaucoma, retinal detachment, skeletal, and joint abnormalities.

results.name: Type III Acrocephalosyndactyly
results.definition: A rare autosomal dominant syndrome caused by mutations in the TWIST1 gene. It is characterized by premature closure of skull bones resulting in abnormally shaped head, high forehead, hypertelorism, and facial asymmetry. It may be associated with fusion of certain fingers or toes.

results.name: Diabetic Ketoacidosis
results.definition: The metabolic condition resulted from uncontrolled diabetes mellitus, in which the shift of acid-base status of the body toward the acid side because of loss of base or retention of acids other than carbonic acid is accompanied by the accumulation of ketone bodies in body tissues and fluids.
results.glossary_definition: A type of metabolic acidosis produced by accumulation of ketone bodies resulting from uncontrolled diabetes mellitus.

results.name: Paronychia
results.definition: An acute or chronic infection of the soft tissues around the nail. Symptoms include pain, tenderness, erythema, and swelling around the nail. Acute infection results from minor trauma to the fingertip and Staphylococcus aureus is usually the causative agent. Chronic infection is usually caused by Candida albicans.
results.glossary_definition: A disorder characterized by an infectious process involving the soft tissues around the nail.

results.name: Cervical Mucinous Adenocarcinoma, Intestinal Variant
results.definition: A cervical mucinous adenocarcinoma that resembles the large intestinal adenocarcinoma.

results.name: Hyperuricemia
results.definition: Elevated blood concentrations of uric acid.
results.glossary_definition: A buildup of uric acid (a byproduct of metabolism) in the blood. Hyperuricemia is a side effect of some anticancer drugs.

results.name: Schistosoma Japonicum Infection
results.definition: An infection that is caused by Schistosoma japonicum.
results.glossary_definition: Schistosomiasis caused by Schistosoma japonicum. It is endemic in the Far East and affects the bowel, liver, and spleen,

results.name: Lymphoid Leukemia
results.definition: A malignant lymphocytic neoplasm of B-cell or T-cell lineage involving primarily the bone marrow and the peripheral blood. This category includes precursor or acute lymphoblastic leukemias and chronic leukemias.
results.glossary_definition: A type of cancer in which the bone marrow makes too many lymphocytes (white blood cells).

results.name: Simultanagnosia
results.definition: A symptom describing the inability to comprehend more than one element of a visual picture at a given moment, or to integrate the whole visual picture.

results.name: Urethral Urothelial Papilloma
results.definition: Papilloma's are benign epithelial neoplasms that produce visible warty projections from epithelial surfaces. Papilloma's of the urethra typically occur just within or on the external meatus. - 2003

results.name: Breast Apocrine Adenosis
results.definition: Breast adenosis characterized by the presence of extensive apocrine metaplasia.

results.name: Nodular Hidradenoma
results.definition: A benign epithelial neoplasm arising from the sweat glands. It presents as a nodular lesion usually in the scalp, trunk, and proximal extremities. It is characterized by a nodular growth pattern. Complete excision is curative.

results.name: Immature Teratoma
results.definition: A teratoma composed of immature, fetal-type tissues.
results.glossary_definition: A rare type of malignant (cancer) germ cell tumor (type of tumor that begins in the cells that give rise to sperm or eggs) that often contains several different types of tissue such as hair, muscle, and bone.

results.name: Adult Central Nervous System Embryonal Carcinoma
results.name_text: Adult Central Nervous System Embryonal Carcinoma

Adult Central Nervous System Embryonal Carcinoma
Embryonal Carcinoma of Adult Central Nervous System
Embryonal Carcinoma of the Adult CNS
Embryonal Carcinoma of the Adult Central Nervous System

Adult Central Nervous System Embryonal Carcinoma
Embryonal Carcinoma of Adult Central Nervous System
Embryonal Carcinoma of the Adult CNS
Embryonal Carcinoma of the Adult Central Nervous System

Embryonal Carcinoma of Adult Central Nervous System
Embryonal Carcinoma of the Adult CNS
Embryonal Carcinoma of the Adult Central Nervous System
