Pediatric Testicular Mixed Germ Cell Tumor
results.definition: A malignant mixed germ cell neoplasm that arises from the testis during childhood.
synonyms: Childhood Testicular Mixed Germ Cell Neoplasm
Childhood Testicular Mixed Germ Cell Tumor
Pediatric Testicular Mixed Germ Cell Neoplasm
Pediatric Testicular Mixed Germ Cell Tumor

results.name: Henoch-Schonlein Purpura
results.definition: A systemic, usually self-limited immune complex vasculitis, characterized by immunoglobulin A deposition in the small vessels and kidneys. It is manifested with small hemorrhages in the skin, gastrointestinal symptoms, arthritis, and nephropathy.
results.glossary_definition: A systemic, usually self-limited immune complex vasculitis, characterized by immunoglobulin A deposition in the small vessels and kidneys. It is manifested with small hemorrhages in the skin, gastrointestinal symptoms, arthritis, and nephropathy.

results.name: Hemangioma
results.definition: A benign vascular lesion characterized by the formation of capillary-sized or cavernous vascular channels.
results.glossary_definition: A benign, vascular neoplasm characterized by the formation of capillary-sized vascular channels.
parents: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Fungal Gastritis
results.definition: Gastritis resulting from fungi.

results.name: Ovarian Squamous Cell Carcinoma
results.definition: A usually high grade squamous cell carcinoma that arises from the ovary and is not associated with a germ cell tumor. The prognosis is poor.

results.name: Appendix Adenocarcinoma
results.definition: A malignant neoplasm arising from the glandular epithelium of the appendix with invasion of the appendiceal wall beyond the muscularis mucosa. The majority of cases are well differentiated adenocarcinomas with mucinous stroma formation. Clinically, it may present as an abdominal mass or with symptoms of acute appendicitis. Patients with chronic ulcerative colitis are at a higher risk in developing appendiceal adenocarcinomas compared to the general population.
children: Colonic Type Adenocarcinoma of the Appendix

results.name: Anthracosilicosis
results.definition: Fibrosis of the lung parenchyma caused by inhalation of carbon and silica dust. It manifests as shortness of breath.
results.glossary_definition: A mixed condition of anthracosis and silicosis. (Dorland, 27th ed)

results.name: Myositis Ossificans
results.definition: A disorder characterized by non-neoplastic bone formation in soft tissues. It usually follows blunt trauma and bleeding in the deep soft tissues.
results.glossary_definition: A disease characterized by bony deposits or the ossification of muscle tissue.

results.name: Pulmonary Embolism
results.definition: The obstruction of the pulmonary artery or one of its branches by an embolus, sometimes associated with infarction of the lung.
results.glossary_definition: The obstruction of the pulmonary artery or one of its branches by an embolus, sometimes associated with infarction of the lung.

results.name: Lung Hilum Neoplasm
results.definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm that arises from the hilar region of the lung.

results.name: Parotitis
results.definition: Inflammation of the parotid glands.
results.glossary_definition: Inflammation of the parotid glands.

results.name: Uterine Corpus Atypical Polypoid Adenomyoma
results.definition: An adenomyoma that arises from the uterine corpus and is characterized by the presence of marked glandular architectural complexity. It may recur following excision.

results.name: Scheie Syndrome
results.definition: An autosomal recessive disorder representing the milder form of mucopolysaccharidosis type I. It is characterized by deficiency of the enzyme alpha-L-iduronidase. Signs and symptoms include broad mouth with full lips, cloudy cornea which may lead to blindness, stiff joints, and hirsutism.

results.name: Hypochondriasis
results.definition: A somatoform disorder in which an individual is preoccupied with having a serious illness despite not having been given a corroborating diagnosis.
results.glossary_definition: Preoccupation with the fear of having, or the idea that one has, a serious disease based on the person's misinterpretation of bodily symptoms. (APA, DSM-IV)

results.name: Childhood Ovarian Immature Teratoma
match: Childhood Immature Teratoma of the Ovary
Pediatric Immature Teratoma of the Ovary
search: Childhood Immature Teratoma of the Ovary
Pediatric Immature Teratoma of the Ovary
results.definition: An immature teratoma that arises from the ovary and occurs in children.
synonyms: Childhood Immature Teratoma of the Ovary
Pediatric Immature Teratoma of the Ovary
parents: Childhood Malignant Ovarian Germ Cell Tumor
ancestors: Childhood Malignant Ovarian Germ Cell Tumor

results.name: Tuberculum Sellae Meningioma
results.definition: A meningioma that affects the tuberculum sellae.

results.name: Language Disorder
results.definition: A category of disorders characterized by an impairment in the development of an individual's language capabilities, which is in contrast to his/her non-verbal intellect.

results.name: Angiosarcoma
results.definition: A malignant tumor arising from the endothelial cells of the blood vessels. Microscopically, it is characterized by frequently open vascular anastomosing and branching channels. The malignant cells that line the vascular channels are spindle or epithelioid and often display hyperchromatic nuclei. Angiosarcomas most frequently occur in the skin and breast. Patients with long-standing lymphedema are at increased risk of developing angiosarcoma.
results.glossary_definition: A type of cancer that begins in the cells that line blood vessels.

results.name: Mucoepidermoid Breast Carcinoma
results.definition: A carcinoma of the breast characterized by pools of mucin and islands of malignant squamous cells. Mucoepidermoid carcinomas of the breast are extremely rare.

results.name: Congenital Epulis
results.definition: A congenital gingival tumor that occurs along the alveolar ridge of the maxilla. It usually affects female infants. The histogenesis is unknown. Morphologically, it is characterized by the presence of large cells with eosinophilic granular cytoplasm. Complete surgical resection is curative.

results.name: Bone Neoplasm
results.definition: A benign, intermediate, or malignant neoplasm involving the bone or articular cartilage.
results.glossary_definition: Neoplasms composed of bony tissue, whether normal or of a soft tissue which has become ossified. The concept does not refer to neoplasms located in bones.
children: Osteoclastic Giant Cell-Rich Tumor of Bone

results.name: Acquired Immunodeficiency Syndrome
results.definition: A syndrome resulting from the acquired deficiency of cellular immunity caused by the human immunodeficiency virus (HIV). It is characterized by the reduction of the Helper T-lymphocytes in the peripheral blood and the lymph nodes. Symptoms include generalized lymphadenopathy, fever, weight loss, and chronic diarrhea. Patients with AIDS are especially susceptible to opportunistic infections (usually pneumocystis carinii pneumonia, cytomegalovirus (CMV) infections, tuberculosis, candida infections, and cryptococcosis), and the development of malignant neoplasms (usually non-Hodgkin lymphoma and Kaposi sarcoma). The human immunodeficiency virus is transmitted through sexual contact, sharing of contaminated needles, or transfusion of contaminated blood.
results.glossary_definition: A disease caused by human immunodeficiency virus (HIV). People with acquired immunodeficiency syndrome are at an increased risk for developing certain cancers and for infections that usually occur only in individuals with a weak immune system.

results.name: Facioscapulohumeral Muscular Dystrophy
results.definition: An autosomal dominant disorder affecting the skeletal muscles of the face, scapula, and upper arm. Patients present with muscle weakness in these anatomic areas. The muscle weakness eventually spreads to other skeletal muscles as well.

results.name: Pineal Gland Astrocytoma
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Gingival Polyp
results.definition: A non-neoplastic nodular lesion that arises from the gingiva.

results.name: Ventricular Septal Defect
results.definition: The presence of a defect (opening) in the septum that separates the two ventricles of the heart. It can be congenital or acquired.
results.glossary_definition: The presence of a defect (opening) in the septum that separates the two ventricles of the heart. The VSD can be congenital or acquired.

results.name: Spindle Cell (Sarcomatoid) Squamous Cell Skin Carcinoma
results.name_text: Spindle Cell (Sarcomatoid) Squamous Cell Skin Carcinoma

Spindle Cell Squamous Carcinoma of Skin

results.name: Sexual Masochism
results.definition: A disorder characterized by recurrent sexual urges, fantasies, or behaviors involving the act (real, not simulated) of being humiliated, beaten, bound, or otherwise made to suffer.

results.name: Q Fever
results.definition: A bacterial infection caused by Coxiella burnetii. It is transmitted to humans by the inhalation of infected air particles or contact with fluids and feces of infected animals. Signs and symptoms include the abrupt onset of fever, headache, myalgias, and weakness.
results.glossary_definition: An acute infectious disease caused by COXIELLA BURNETII. It is characterized by a sudden onset of fever, headache, malaise, and weakness. In humans, it is commonly contracted by inhalation of infected dusts derived from infected domestic animals.

results.name: Hypokalemic Periodic Paralysis
results.definition: A rare, autosomal dominant inherited disorder characterized by irregular episodes of muscle weakness or paralysis which are always accompanied by low levels of potassium in the blood.

results.name: Nasopharyngeal Type Undifferentiated Carcinoma
results.definition: A nonkeratinizing carcinoma which occurs predominantly in the nasopharynx but also in the tonsils and rarely in other anatomic sites. It is characterized by the presence of large malignant cells with vesicular nuclei, prominent nucleoli, syncytial growth pattern, and a lymphoplasmacytic infiltrate.

results.name: Blastema Predominant Kidney Wilms Tumor
results.definition: Wilms tumor of the kidney characterized by the predominance of the blastema component.

results.name: Bronchiolitis
results.definition: Inflammation of the bronchioles characterized by swelling of the bronchioles and mucus accumulation. It is usually caused by the respiratory syncytial virus and affects children. Signs and symptoms include coughing, wheezing, and shortness of breath.
results.glossary_definition: Inflammation of the bronchioles.

results.name: Gallbladder Lymphoma
results.definition: A lymphoma that arises from the gallbladder, with the bulk of the tumor located at this site.

results.name: Hypochondroplasia
results.definition: An autosomal dominant disorder that is often caused by a defect in fibroblast growth factor receptor 3, and characterized by short stature, micromelia, and a comparatively large head. The features are milder than those seen in achondroplasia.

results.name: Mediastinal Neuroblastoma
results.definition: A neuroblastoma arising from the mediastinum.
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Ciliary Motility Defect
results.definition: Defective movements of the cilia. It includes abnormal movements of the cilia in the nose and paranasal sinuses, the respiratory tract and spermatozoa.

results.name: Male Orgasmic Disorder
results.definition: Persistent delay or absence in orgasm not accounted for by a medical reason.

results.name: Cystitis Cystica
results.definition: A reactive inflammatory disorder affecting the bladder. It is characterized by the development of small cysts in the bladder wall. The cysts are lined by urothelial cells.

results.name: Gestational Diabetes
results.definition: Carbohydrate intolerance first diagnosed during pregnancy.
results.glossary_definition: Carbohydrate intolerance first diagnosed during pregnancy.

results.name: Ethmoid Sinus Schneiderian Papilloma
match: Schneiderian Papilloma of the Ethmoid Sinus
search: Schneiderian Papilloma of the Ethmoid Sinus
results.definition: A papilloma that arises from the ciliated respiratory mucosa that lines the ethmoid sinus. It is classified as inverted papilloma and oncocytic papilloma.
synonyms: Schneiderian Papilloma of the Ethmoid Sinus

results.name: Antisocial Personality Disorder
results.definition: A disorder characterized by a pervasive pattern of disregard for and violation of the rights of others that is manifested in childhood or early adolescence. (adapted from DSM-IV)

results.name: Vulvar Adenocarcinoma
results.definition: An adenocarcinoma that arises from the vulva. Representative examples include Bartholin gland adenocarcinoma, eccrine adenocarcinoma, apocrine adenocarcinoma, and sebaceous carcinoma.
children: Vulvar Adenocarcinoma of Sweat Gland Type

results.name: Citrullinemia
results.definition: A rare autosomal recessive inherited disorder caused by mutations in the ASS1 and SLC25A13 genes. It is characterized by a defective urea cycle, resulting in the accumulation of ammonia and other toxic substances in the blood.

results.name: Tumor of the Follicular Infundibulum
match: Basal Cell Hamartoma with Follicular Differentiation
search: Basal Cell Hamartoma with Follicular Differentiation
synonyms: Basal Cell Hamartoma with Follicular Differentiation

results.name: Esophageal Basaloid Carcinoma
match: Basaloid Squamous Carcinoma of the Esophagus
search: Basaloid Squamous Carcinoma of the Esophagus
results.definition: A rare morphologic variant of esophageal squamous cell carcinoma. Histologically, it is composed of closely packed cells with hyperchromatic nuclei and scant basophilic cytoplasm. It has a similar prognosis to the conventional squamous cell carcinoma of the esophagus. (WHO)
synonyms: Basaloid Squamous Carcinoma of the Esophagus

results.name: Adenofibroma
results.definition: A benign neoplasm characterized by the presence of connective tissue stroma and epithelial structures. It occurs in the ovary, fallopian tube, uterine corpus, and cervix. Cases of adenofibroma of the ovary with low grade malignant potential have also been reported.
results.glossary_definition: Benign mixed neoplasm comprised of epithelial/glandular and mesenchymal structures.

results.name: Ovarian Small Cell Carcinoma, Hypercalcemic Type
results.name_text: Ovarian Small Cell Carcinoma, Hypercalcemic Type
match: Ovarian Small Cell Carcinoma, Hypercalcemic Type
Ovarian Small Cell Carcinoma, Hypercalcemic Type
search: Ovarian Small Cell Carcinoma, Hypercalcemic Type
Ovarian Small Cell Carcinoma, Hypercalcemic Type
results.definition: An undifferentiated small cell carcinoma that arises from the ovary and is associated with hypercalcemia. Electron microscopic studies show neurosecretory granules are either absent or, when present, are in small numbers.
synonyms: Ovarian Small Cell Carcinoma, Hypercalcemic Type

results.name: Diffuse Idiopathic Skeletal Hyperostosis
results.definition: A rare degenerative disorder that affects the spine. It is characterized by ossification of ligaments resulting in calcifications along the sides of the spinal vertebrae.

results.name: Graves Disease
results.definition: Hyperthyroidism associated with diffuse hyperplasia of the thyroid gland (goiter), resulting from production of antibodies that are directed against the thyrotropin receptor complex of the follicular epithelial cells. As a result, the thyroid gland enlarges and secrets increased amounts of thyroid hormones.
results.glossary_definition: Hyperthyroidism associated with a diffuse hyperplastic goiter resulting from production of an antibody directed against the thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH) receptor, which acts as an agonist of TSH. (Braverman, The Thyroid, 6th ed, p648)

results.name: Acute Myocarditis
results.definition: The sudden onset of inflammation of heart muscle with myocellular necrosis; this is generally secondary to an infectious cause, and patients often have a recent history of a flu-like illness.

results.name: Small Intestinal Sarcoma
results.definition: A malignant soft tissue neoplasm that arises from the small intestine. Representative examples include leiomyosarcoma, angiosarcoma, and Kaposi sarcoma.

results.name: Childhood Kidney Angiomyolipoma
results.definition: An angiomyolipoma occurring in childhood.

results.name: Cranial Nodular Fasciitis
results.definition: A rare self-limiting, rapidly growing, non-encapsulated benign neoplasm that arises from the cranium. This is an osteolytic lesion. It is characterized by the presence of plump spindle-shaped fibroblasts, multinucleated osteoclast-like giant cells, chronic inflammatory infiltrate, red blood cell extravasation, and high mitotic activity.
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Alpha Thalassemia
results.definition: A genetic hematologic disorder characterized by partial or complete absence of the alpha globin chains of the heme molecule.
results.glossary_definition: A disorder characterized by reduced synthesis of the alpha chains of hemoglobin. The severity of this condition can vary from mild anemia to death, depending on the number of genes deleted.

results.name: Hereditary Papillary Renal Cell Carcinoma
match: Hereditary Papillary Carcinoma of the Kidney
search: Hereditary Papillary Carcinoma of the Kidney
results.definition: A familial carcinoma inherited in an autosomal dominant trait. It is characterized by the development of multiple, bilateral papillary renal cell carcinomas. The carcinomas range from microscopic lesions to clinically symptomatic tumors. It is associated with activating mutations of the MET oncogene.
synonyms: Hereditary Papillary Carcinoma of the Kidney

results.name: Adult Spinal Cord Glioblastoma
results.definition: A rare spinal tumor which is highly malignant and tends to be locally invasive of surrounding neural tissue. The tumor also tends to spread throughout the neuroaxis and is often rapidly progressive. Histologically the tumors are highly cellular with nuclear and cellular pleomorphism, endothelial proliferation, mitotic figures, and, often, necrosis. This tumor has a relatively poor prognosis. Clinical features may include pain followed by rapidly progressive neurologic deficits such as extremity weakness, sensory changes, spasticity, and incontinence. (From Innocenzi et al., Clin Neurol Neurosurg 1997 Feb;99(1):1-5)
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Ectomesenchymoma
match: Sarcoma with Ganglionic or Neuroectodermal Differentiation
search: Sarcoma with Ganglionic or Neuroectodermal Differentiation
results.definition: An aggressive malignant mesenchymal neoplasm of the nervous system or soft tissues. It is characterized by the presence of a sarcomatous component (most often rhabdomyosarcoma) and a ganglionic or a neuroectodermal component.
results.glossary_definition: A rare, fast-growing tumor of the nervous system or soft tissue that occurs in children and young adults. Ectomesenchymomas may form in the head and neck, abdomen, perineum, scrotum, or limbs.
synonyms: Sarcoma with Ganglionic or Neuroectodermal Differentiation
parents: Central Nervous System Mesenchymal Non-meningothelial Tumor
ancestors: Central Nervous System Mesenchymal Non-meningothelial Tumor

results.name: Nodular Sclerosis Classical Hodgkin Lymphoma
results.definition: A subtype of classical Hodgkin lymphoma characterized by collagen bands that surround at least one nodule, and Hodgkin and Reed-Sternberg cells with lacunar type morphology. (WHO, 2008)

results.name: Ureter Abscess
results.definition: An abscess that is located in the ureter.

results.name: Bladder Sarcoma
results.definition: A malignant mesenchymal cell neoplasm that affects the urinary bladder.

results.name: Juvenile Xanthogranuloma
results.definition: A benign histiocytic tumor that occurs during childhood; it is distinct from Langerhans cell histiocytosis. It is characterized by the presence of lipid-laden, foamy histiocytes and Touton-type giant cells in the dermis. The lesions usually develop during infancy. They consist of cutaneous papules and nodules (most often in the head and neck). It is sometimes associated with deep soft tissues nodules.
results.glossary_definition: Benign disorder of infants and children characterized by multiple nodules with lipid-laden, non-Langerhans-cell histiocytes.

results.name: Intraductal Proliferative Lesion of the Breast
results.name_text: Intraductal Proliferative Lesion of the Breast
match: Intraductal Proliferative Lesion of the Breast
Intraductal Proliferative Lesion of the Breast
search: Intraductal Proliferative Lesion of the Breast
Intraductal Proliferative Lesion of the Breast
results.definition: A group of non-invasive epithelial proliferations that occur in the ductal system of the breast. The vast majority of cases arise in the terminal ductal lobular units. This category includes atypical ductal hyperplasia, usual ductal hyperplasia, flat epithelial atypia, and ductal carcinoma in situ. There is an increased risk for subsequent development of invasive breast carcinoma.
synonyms: Intraductal Proliferative Lesion of the Breast

results.name: Anti-Basement Membrane Glomerulonephritis
results.definition: Inflammation of the glomeruli secondary to presence of autoantibodies directed at specific antigenic targets within the glomerular basement membrane, causing hematuria, proteinuria, and impaired renal function.

results.name: Intermediate Cell Type Iris Melanoma
results.definition: Iris melanoma characterized by the presence of intermediate cells which are similar to but smaller than epithelioid cells.

results.name: Supravalvular Aortic Stenosis
results.definition: A rare, congenital or acquired aortic stenosis characterized by localized or diffuse narrowing of the ascending aorta.

results.name: Hair Follicle Neoplasm
results.definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm arising from the hair follicle.
results.glossary_definition: A neoplasm that arises from the hair follicle, for which the malignancy status has not been established.

results.name: Benign Breast Adenomyoepithelioma
results.definition: A benign, nodular tumor that arises from the breast parenchyma. It is characterized by the proliferation of myoepithelial cells around spaces that are lined by epithelial cells. Occasionally, adenomyoepitheliomas may undergo malignant transformation.

results.name: Gallbladder Obstruction
results.definition: Blockage of the normal flow of the contents of the gallbladder.
results.glossary_definition: A disorder characterized by blockage of the normal flow of the contents of the gallbladder.

results.name: Clear Cell Adenocarcinoma
results.definition: A malignant neoplasm composed of glandular epithelial clear cells. Various architectural patterns may be seen, including papillary, tubulocystic, and solid.
results.glossary_definition: A rare type of tumor, usually of the female genital tract, in which the insides of the cells look clear when viewed under a microscope.
children: Ampulla of Vater Clear Cell Adenocarcinoma
Extrahepatic Bile Duct Clear Cell Adenocarcinoma

results.name: Sideroblastic Anemia
results.definition: Anemia characterized by the production of ringed sideroblasts instead of healthy red blood cells.

results.name: Mixed Connective Tissue Disease
results.definition: An autoimmune overlap syndrome characterized by the presence of symptoms of systemic lupus erythematosus, systemic scleroderma, and polymyositis.
results.glossary_definition: An autoimmune disorder which is associated with high titer anti-RNP antibody, and usually features Raynaud's Phenomenon and swollen fingers.

results.definition: A multinodular intermediate fibroblastic neoplasm that arises from soft tissue or viscera, in children and young adults. It is characterized by the presence of spindle-shaped fibroblasts and myofibroblasts, and a chronic inflammatory infiltrate composed of eosinophils, lymphocytes, and plasma cells.
results.name: Inflammatory Myofibroblastic Tumor
Substance Abuse
results.definition: Maladaptive pattern of drug or alcohol use that may lead to social, occupational, psychological, or physical problems.
results.glossary_definition: The use of illegal drugs or the use of prescription or over-the-counter drugs or alcohol for purposes other than those for which they are meant to be used, or in excessive amounts. Substance abuse may lead to social, physical, emotional, and job-related problems.

results.name: Internal Hemorrhoid
results.definition: A hemorrhoid which originates above the dentate line.

results.name: Mitral Valve Prolapse
results.definition: A fairly common and often benign valvular heart disorder characterized by redundancy or hooding of mitral valve leaflets so that they prolapse into the left atrium, often causing mitral regurgitation. It is often a symptomless condition but may be marked by varied symptoms (e.g. chest pain, fatigue, dizziness, dyspnea, or palpitations) leading in some cases to endocarditis or ventricular tachycardia.
results.glossary_definition: Prolapse of the mitral valve, often with regurgitation, associated with myxomatous proliferation of the leaflets of the mitral valve.

results.name: Spinocerebellar Ataxia
results.definition: An inherited disorder characterized by degeneration of the spinal cord and the cerebellum. Symptoms may appear at any age and include progressive loss of coordination of gait, hands, speech, and eye movements.

results.name: Patent Foramen Ovale
results.definition: A persistent opening in the atrial septum after birth. While a normal part of fetal circulation, the foramen ovale should close once the newborn begins breathing and the pressure in the left atrium exceeds that of the right atrium. While a PFO is generally asymptomatic, it can lead to the passage of clots from the venous circulation into the artierial circulation, resulting in paradoxical emboli, and possible strokes.

results.name: Uterine Corpus Leiomyoma
match: Fibroid of the Body of Uterus
Leiomyoma of the Body of Uterus
search: Fibroid of the Body of Uterus
Leiomyoma of the Body of Uterus
results.definition: A benign smooth muscle neoplasm arising from the body of the uterus. It is characterized by the presence of spindle cells with cigar-shaped nuclei, interlacing fascicles, and a whorled pattern.
synonyms: Fibroid of the Body of Uterus
Leiomyoma of the Body of Uterus
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Allergic Contact Dermatitis
results.definition: An inflammatory skin condition caused by an immune response to direct contact between the skin and an allergen. It consists of a delayed type of allergic reaction at the affected site with resulting red, swollen, and blistered skin that may itch or leak.
results.glossary_definition: A contact dermatitis due to allergic sensitization to various substances. These substances subsequently produce inflammatory reactions in the skin of those who have acquired hypersensitivity to them as a result of prior exposure.

results.name: Ovarian Malignant Mesothelioma
results.definition: A rare malignant mesothelial neoplasm that usually involves both the ovarian surface and the ovarian stroma. In most cases there is bilateral ovarian involvement.

results.name: Ovarian Clear Cell Adenocarcinoma
results.definition: A malignant glandular epithelial neoplasm characterized by the presence of clear and hobnail cells. It is highly associated with ovarian endometriosis, pelvic endometriosis and paraendocrine hypercalcemia.

results.name: Ovarian Brenner Tumor
results.definition: A benign, borderline, or malignant transitional cell neoplasm arising from the ovary. It constitutes between 1% and 2% of all ovarian neoplasms. The average age at presentation is about 50 years. Grossly it is usually unilateral, firm and white or yellowish. Microscopically it consists of solid and cystic nests of epithelial cells resembling transitional epithelium surrounded by an abundant stromal component of dense, fibroblastic nature.

results.name: Friedreich Ataxia
results.definition: An autosomal recessive inherited disorder caused by mutations in the FXN gene. It is characterized by progressive degeneration of the nerve tissues of the spinal cord. The main symptoms include gait and balance disturbances, lack of limb coordination, and speech disturbances.

results.name: Urethral Stricture
results.definition: Narrowing of the lumen of the urethra.

results.name: Benign Mixed Tumor of the Vulva
results.name_text: Benign Mixed Tumor of the Vulva
match: Benign Mixed Tumor of the Vulva
Benign Mixed Tumor of the Vulva
search: Benign Mixed Tumor of the Vulva
Benign Mixed Tumor of the Vulva
results.definition: A benign neoplasm that arises from the vulva and is characterized by the presence of epithelial cells forming nests and tubules in a fibrotic stroma. It may recur locally and complete excision is recommended.
synonyms: Benign Mixed Tumor of the Vulva

results.name: Testicular Monophasic Choriocarcinoma
results.definition: A choriocarcinoma that arises from the testis and is characterized by the predominance of cytotrophoblastic and intermediate trophoblastic cells. Syncytiotrophoblastic cells are absent or not prominent.
ancestors: Malignant Testicular Non-Seminomatous Germ Cell Tumor

results.name: Lung Adenoma
results.definition: A benign, well circumscribed epithelial neoplasm that arises from the bronchus or the lung parenchyma. Representative examples include alveolar adenoma, papillary adenoma, and mucus gland adenoma.

results.name: Undifferentiated High Grade Pleomorphic Sarcoma of Bone
results.name_text: Undifferentiated High Grade Pleomorphic Sarcoma of Bone
match: Undifferentiated High Grade Pleomorphic Sarcoma of Bone
Malignant Fibrous Histiocytoma of the Bone
Undifferentiated High Grade Pleomorphic Sarcoma of Bone
search: Undifferentiated High Grade Pleomorphic Sarcoma of Bone
Malignant Fibrous Histiocytoma of the Bone
Undifferentiated High Grade Pleomorphic Sarcoma of Bone
results.definition: A rare, high-grade pleomorphic malignant neoplasm arising from the bone. It usually presents with pain which may or may not be associated with swelling in the affected area. It is characterized by the presence of spindle-shaped cells, polygonal or epithelioid cells, multinucleated giant cells, and inflammatory cells. The neoplastic cells exhibit nuclear pleomorphism and high mitotic activity. It metastasizes frequently, most often in the lungs.
synonyms: Malignant Fibrous Histiocytoma of the Bone
Undifferentiated High Grade Pleomorphic Sarcoma of Bone
ancestors: Malignant Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Cerebellar Astrocytoma
results.definition: Benign and malignant neoplasms of the cerebellum that arise from astrocytes. During childhood the majority are benign pilocytic astrocytomas. In adults both benign and relatively higher grade forms may occur. The most common presenting symptoms are headache, nausea, vomiting, ataxia of gait or limb, paresis, diplopia, and dizziness. Objective signs include weakness, long tract signs, dysmetria, gait ataxia, papilledema, and nystagmus. Surgical resection is often curative.
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Fallopian Tube Transitional Cell Carcinoma
results.definition: A rare transitional cell carcinoma that arises from the fallopian tube.

results.name: Digestive System Neuroendocrine Neoplasm
results.definition: A neoplasm with neuroendocrine differentiation arising from the digestive system. It includes neuroendocrine tumors (well-differentiated endocrine tumors or carcinoid tumors and well differentiated endocrine carcinomas) and neuroendocrine carcinomas (poorly differentiated neuroendocrine carcinomas, small cell carcinomas, and large cell neuroendocrine carcinomas).

results.name: Anaplastic Astrocytoma
results.definition: A diffusely infiltrating, WHO grade III astrocytoma with focal or dispersed anaplasia, and a marked proliferative potential. It may arise from a low-grade astrocytoma, but it can also be diagnosed at first biopsy, without indication of a less malignant precursor lesion. It has an intrinsic tendency for malignant progression to glioblastoma. (WHO)
results.glossary_definition: A malignant neoplasm of the brain or spinal cord originating from astrocytes, exhibiting poor differentiation (anaplasia).
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Penile Neoplasm
results.definition: A benign, borderline, or malignant neoplasm that affects the penis. Representative examples include penile hemangioma, penile intraepithelial neoplasia, and penile carcinoma.
results.glossary_definition: Cancers or tumors of the PENIS or of its component tissues.

results.name: Childhood Testicular Choriocarcinoma
results.definition: A choriocarcinoma that arises from the testis during childhood.
ancestors: Malignant Testicular Non-Seminomatous Germ Cell Tumor

results.name: Spinal Muscular Atrophy
results.definition: An inherited disorder characterized by degeneration of the spinal cord and the cerebellum. Symptoms may appear at any age and include progressive loss of coordination of gait, hands, speech, and eye movements.

results.name: Renal Tubular Acidosis
results.definition: The inability of the kidneys to maintain acid-base homeostasis.
results.glossary_definition: A rare disorder in which structures in the kidney that filter the blood are impaired, producing urine that is more acid than normal.

results.name: Spindle Cell Hemangioma
results.definition: A hemangioma characterized by the presence of spindle endothelial cells.
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Pancreatoblastoma
results.definition: A rare malignant epithelial neoplasm arising from the pancreas. The vast majority of cases occur during childhood. It is characterized by acinar differentiation, the formation of squamoid corpuscles, and the formation of stromal bands. Patients may present with an abdominal mass. Symptoms include pain, weight loss, and diarrhea. It may metastasize to lymph nodes, liver, and distant anatomic sites. Children who do not have metastatic disease at the time of diagnosis usually have a favorable clinical outcome when treated with a combination of surgery and chemotherapy. However, children with metastatic disease at presentation or adult patients usually have a poor prognosis.

results.name: Ruptured Aortic Aneurysm
results.definition: A ruptured aneurysm located in the wall of the aorta.

results.name: Malignant Eccrine Neoplasm
match: Malignant Eccrine Neoplasm of the Skin
Malignant Eccrine Tumor of the Skin
search: Malignant Eccrine Neoplasm of the Skin
Malignant Eccrine Tumor of the Skin
synonyms: Malignant Eccrine Neoplasm of the Skin
Malignant Eccrine Tumor of the Skin

results.name: Peripheral Motor Neuropathy
results.definition: Inflammation or degeneration of the peripheral motor nerves.
results.glossary_definition: A disorder characterized by inflammation or degeneration of the peripheral motor nerves.

results.name: Uterine Corpus Epithelioid Leiomyoma
results.definition: A morphologic variant of uterine corpus leiomyoma characterized by the presence of round or polygonal epithelioid smooth muscle cells forming clusters.
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Ovarian Mucinous Tumor
results.definition: A benign, borderline, or malignant epithelial tumor of the ovary characterized by the presence of neoplastic epithelial cells that contain intracytoplasmic mucin and may resemble the epithelial cells of the endocervix or gastrointestinal tract.

results.name: PEComa
match: Neoplasm with Perivascular Epithelioid Cell Differentiation
Tumor with Perivascular Epithelioid Cell Differentiation
search: Neoplasm with Perivascular Epithelioid Cell Differentiation
Tumor with Perivascular Epithelioid Cell Differentiation
results.definition: A soft tissue mesenchymal tumor with perivascular epithelioid cell differentiation. Representative examples include angiomyolipoma, clear cell-sugar-tumor of the lung, and lymphangioleiomyomatosis.
synonyms: Neoplasm with Perivascular Epithelioid Cell Differentiation
Tumor with Perivascular Epithelioid Cell Differentiation

results.name: Fibrous Meningioma
results.definition: A WHO grade I meningioma characterized by the presence of spindle cells that form bundles in a collagen matrix.

results.name: Paraganglioma
results.definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm arising from paraganglia located along the sympathetic or parasympathetic nerves. Infrequently, it may arise outside the usual distribution of the sympathetic and parasympathetic paraganglia. Tumors arising from the adrenal gland medulla are called pheochromocytomas. Morphologically, paragangliomas usually display a nesting (Zellballen) growth pattern. There are no reliable morphologic criteria to distinguish between benign and malignant paragangliomas. The only definitive indicator of malignancy is the presence of regional or distant metastases.
results.glossary_definition: A rare, usually benign tumor that develops from cells of the paraganglia. Paraganglia are a collection of cells that came from embryonic nervous tissue, and are found near the adrenal glands and some blood vessels and nerves. Paragangliomas that develop in the adrenal gland are called pheochromocytomas. Those that develop outside of the adrenal glands near blood vessels or nerves are called glomus tumors or chemodectomas.

results.name: Acute Conjunctivitis
results.definition: Acute inflammation of the conjunctiva.

A malignant neuroendocrine neoplasm composed of cells containing secretory granules that stain positive for NSE and chromogranin. The neoplastic cells are often round and form clusters or trabecular sheets. Representative examples are small cell carcinoma, large cell neuroendocrine carcinoma, and Merkel cell carcinoma.
results.glossary_definition: A malignant neuroendocrine neoplasm comprising cells containing secretory granules.
results.name: Neuroendocrine Carcinoma
Prolactin-Producing Pituitary Gland Adenoma
match: Prolactin Producing Adenoma of Pituitary Gland
Prolactin Producing Adenoma of the Pituitary Gland
Prolactin Producing Adenoma of the Pituitary
Prolactin Secreting Adenoma of Pituitary Gland
Prolactin Secreting Adenoma of the Pituitary Gland
Prolactin Secreting Adenoma of the Pituitary
search: Prolactin Producing Adenoma of Pituitary Gland
Prolactin Producing Adenoma of the Pituitary Gland
Prolactin Producing Adenoma of the Pituitary
Prolactin Secreting Adenoma of Pituitary Gland
Prolactin Secreting Adenoma of the Pituitary Gland
Prolactin Secreting Adenoma of the Pituitary
results.definition: An adenoma of the anterior lobe of the pituitary gland that produces prolactin. It is the most common type of pituitary gland adenomas and it is associated with hyperprolactinemia. Clinical manifestations include amenorrhea, galactorrhea, impotence, headache, and visual disturbances.
synonyms: Prolactin Producing Adenoma of Pituitary Gland
Prolactin Producing Adenoma of the Pituitary Gland
Prolactin Producing Adenoma of the Pituitary
Prolactin Secreting Adenoma of Pituitary Gland
Prolactin Secreting Adenoma of the Pituitary Gland
Prolactin Secreting Adenoma of the Pituitary

results.name: Hypertrophic Pyloric Stenosis
results.definition: An abnormality characterized by thickening of the muscle in the wall of the pylorus. It results in the narrowing of the pyloric channel. The overlying mucosa may appear hypertrophic as well. Clinical signs and symptoms appear early in life and include projectile vomiting and dehydration.
results.glossary_definition: Narrowing of the pyloric channel, the opening from the stomach to the duodenum, caused by enlargement and thickening of the circular muscular layer surrounding this opening.

results.name: Cavernous Hemangioma
results.definition: A hemangioma characterized by the presence of cavernous vascular spaces.

results.name: Tenosynovial Giant Cell Tumor
match: Giant Cell Neoplasm of Tendon Sheath
Giant Cell Neoplasm of the Tenosynovium
Giant Cell Tumor of Tendon Sheath
Giant Cell Tumor of the Tenosynovium
search: Giant Cell Neoplasm of Tendon Sheath
Giant Cell Neoplasm of the Tenosynovium
Giant Cell Tumor of Tendon Sheath
Giant Cell Tumor of the Tenosynovium
results.definition: A tumor usually arising in the synovium of joints, bursa or tendon sheath. It is characterized by the presence of mononuclear cells, multinucleated osteoclast-like giant cells, hemosiderin-laden macrophages, foam cells, and an inflammatory infiltrate. According to the growth pattern, it is classified as localized or diffuse.
synonyms: Giant Cell Neoplasm of Tendon Sheath
Giant Cell Neoplasm of the Tenosynovium
Giant Cell Tumor of Tendon Sheath
Giant Cell Tumor of the Tenosynovium
children: Tenosynovial Giant Cell Tumor, Diffuse Type

results.name: Brenner Tumor
results.definition: A usually benign tumor composed of solid and cystic nests of epithelial cells resembling transitional epithelium; it is surrounded by an abundant stromal component that is dense and fibroblastic in nature.

results.name: Small Intestinal L-Cell Glucagon-Like Peptide-Producing Neuroendocrine Tumor
results.name_text: Small Intestinal L-Cell Glucagon-Like Peptide-Producing Neuroendocrine Tumor
match: Small Intestinal L-Cell Glucagon-Like Peptide-Producing Neuroendocrine Tumor
Small Intestinal L-Cell Glucagon-Like Peptide-Producing NET
Small Intestinal L-Cell Glucagon-Like Peptide-Producing Neuroendocrine Tumor
Small Intestinal L-Cell, Glucagon-Like Peptide-Producing Neuroendocrine Tumor
search: Small Intestinal L-Cell Glucagon-Like Peptide-Producing Neuroendocrine Tumor
Small Intestinal L-Cell Glucagon-Like Peptide-Producing NET
Small Intestinal L-Cell Glucagon-Like Peptide-Producing Neuroendocrine Tumor
Small Intestinal L-Cell, Glucagon-Like Peptide-Producing Neuroendocrine Tumor
results.definition: A neuroendocrine tumor that arises from the small intestine and produces glucagon-like peptides. Morphologically, it is characterized by the presence of neoplastic cells forming tubular or trabecular patterns.
synonyms: Small Intestinal L-Cell Glucagon-Like Peptide-Producing NET
Small Intestinal L-Cell Glucagon-Like Peptide-Producing Neuroendocrine Tumor
Small Intestinal L-Cell, Glucagon-Like Peptide-Producing Neuroendocrine Tumor

results.name: Congenital Combined Immunodeficiency
results.definition: A broad classification of inherited disorders presenting at birth that affect both the cell-mediated and humoral aspects of the immune response. Circulating numbers of B lymphocytes, T lymphocytes and NK cells are variable but where present do not function properly. Susceptibility to infection is the primary concern.

results.name: Tracheal Stenosis
results.definition: Narrowing of the lumen of the trachea.
results.glossary_definition: A disorder characterized by a narrowing of the trachea.

results.name: Adrenal Gland Disorder
results.definition: Any disease affecting the adrenal gland.

results.name: Childhood Botryoid-Type Embryonal Rhabdomyosarcoma of the Vulva
results.name_text: Childhood Botryoid-Type Embryonal Rhabdomyosarcoma of the Vulva
match: Childhood Botryoid-Type Embryonal Rhabdomyosarcoma of the Vulva
Childhood Botryoid-Type Embryonal Rhabdomyosarcoma of the Vulva
Childhood Sarcoma Botryoides of the Vulva
search: Childhood Botryoid-Type Embryonal Rhabdomyosarcoma of the Vulva
Childhood Botryoid-Type Embryonal Rhabdomyosarcoma of the Vulva
Childhood Sarcoma Botryoides of the Vulva
results.definition: A morphologic variant of embryonal rhabdomyosarcoma occurring in female children. The neoplasm arises from the vulva. It is characterized by the formation of a cambium layer in the affected tissue and polypoid nodules with an abundant myxoid stroma.
synonyms: Childhood Botryoid-Type Embryonal Rhabdomyosarcoma of the Vulva
Childhood Sarcoma Botryoides of the Vulva

results.name: Colorectal Adenocarcinoma
results.definition: The most common type of colorectal carcinoma. It is characterized by the presence of malignant glandular epithelial cells invading through the muscularis mucosa into the submucosa. Histologic variants include mucinous adenocarcinoma, signet ring cell carcinoma, medullary carcinoma, serrated adenocarcinoma, cribriform comedo-type adenocarcinoma, and micropapillary adenocarcinoma.

results.name: Gyrate Atrophy
results.definition: A rare autosomal recessive inherited disorder caused by mutations in the OAT gene. It is characterized by progressive atrophy of the retina and choroid, leading to loss of vision and blindness.

results.name: Adult Extraskeletal Osteosarcoma
results.definition: An osteosarcoma arising from the soft tissue, and occurring in adults.
ancestors: Malignant Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Paranoid Personality Disorder
results.definition: A disorder characterized by an enduring pattern of behavior based on the pervasive belief that the motives of others are malevolent and that they should not be trusted.

results.name: Vaginal Squamous Papilloma
results.definition: A benign papillary neoplasm that arises from the vagina and is characterized by the presence of a fibrovascular stalk lined by normal squamous epithelium. There is no evidence of atypia or relation to human papillomavirus.

results.name: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Microcystic Pattern
results.name_text: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Microcystic Pattern
match: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Microcystic Pattern
Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Microcystic Pattern
Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Reticular Pattern
search: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Microcystic Pattern
Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Microcystic Pattern
Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Reticular Pattern
results.definition: A yolk sac tumor that arises from the testis and is characterized by the presence of a meshwork of small vacuolated cells resulting in a honeycomb appearance.
synonyms: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Microcystic Pattern
Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Reticular Pattern
ancestors: Malignant Testicular Non-Seminomatous Germ Cell Tumor

results.name: Central Hearing Loss
results.definition: Hearing loss resulting from disorders of the central nervous system auditory pathways.
results.glossary_definition: Hearing loss resulting from disorders of the central nervous system auditory pathways.

results.name: Sarcomatosis

results.definition: An autosomal recessive inherited peroxisomal disorder caused by mutations in the PEX7, DHAPAT, and AGP genes. It is characterized by short limbs, bones and cartilage abnormalities, congenital cataracts, and severe mental retardation.
